animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Elijah

DOB: 7/4/2016

Weight: 40 lbs

Adoption Fee: $375.00

Hello, I'm Elijah! I just finished my heartworm treatment and I am ready to play! I love other dogs and always want to make friends. Sometimes I'm a little too excited and vocal when I meet new friends, but I know they all secretly want to be my best friend. I'll need someone to make sure I don't play too hard because I miss dogs' cues often and have trouble listening when I'm excited. I really need to run around at the dog park every day if I don't live with other dogs who can tire me out. When I'm inside, you might find me staring out the window at all the action I think I'm missing, or munching on one of many toys because I LOVE to chew. Once I'm tired out, I am the biggest snugglebug (lapdog alert!), and I always want to make sure you know how much I love rubs. And my crocodile, but mostly rubs.

Even though I seem ready for anything, I'm slower to warm up and developed a stronger bond with one of my foster parents than the other. I'll need someone patient to help me know that wearing a sweater and trimming my nails won't hurt me. Sometimes I get scared and snap when I feel afraid, or when I'm eating. I can also be unsure meeting new people when they want to come into my home. I would do best in a home without small children.
I'm kennel trained, I'm getting better at 'drop,' and tugging on my leash. I also love to pounce on bushes and see what I scare up! I'm generally a goofy sweetheart who loves life. I'm highly treat motivated, and I would definitely benefit from obedience classes. With a patient, loving home, I will be an absolute joy full of love to give!

*Elijah recently went through heartworm treatment*

Here is a great article explaining what heartworm is and how it's treated: https://www.heartwormsociety.org/pet-owner-resources/heartworm-basics

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Name: Wyatt
Sex: Male
Breed: Lab Mix
DOB: August 2018
Weight: 60lb
Adoptable in MA, CT and NH

Wyatt is a social, playful two-year-old boy who comes to us originally from Tennessee! He was found in a barn with his mother, Whitney, and sister, Willow. Wyatt loves people and will be absolutely thrilled to see any of them! He loves to go to the state park for a quick jump in the pond. He is an excellent car rider and will let you fashion him to a seat belt so he can ride in style! Wyatt also loves the vet and will be a star whenever he goes due to his love for anyone he meets. He's a sweet, loving dog!

Wyatt has lived with older children and done well, but may jump on the little ones and any strangers he's excited to see. While Wyatt has resided with other animals, he is looking for a pet-free home at this time, as he holds his toys, home and food near and dear to his heart! Wyatt will thrive in a high-energy home with lots of mental stimulation and things to do. He'll love any chance you give him for exercise, so he's a great running buddy!

Wyatt has been crate-trained and quite enjoys spending time in his little den, and will likely benefit from being crated during times someone cannot be home, as he does tend to have wandering paws when he gets bored! He is completely housebroken. He knows his basic commands of come, sit, stay, paw, other paw, down, and up. He absolutely loves to learn, play, and just generally be a dog! If you're looking for a sweet, loving, high-energy dog, Wyatt would be a great addition to your pet-free home.

If you are interested in adopting or fostering, please fill out an application at survivortails.org or email adoptions@survivortails.org with any questions.

Hi there! I'm Scooby Snacks and my foster mom tells me I'm the goodest boy... so I'll take her word for it. I am perfectly house trained and mild mannered. I get so excited to go for a walk, sometimes I'll even run to the door to get my harness on, just not for long distances anymore. I'm more a stop and smell the roses kind of guy. Squirrels are the enemy and don't worry, I will always let you know if there is one near!! I like to stop and say hello to fellow K9 friends when out walking but my play style is more into taking naps together than rough housing! 


I do love to snuggle and I'm known in certain circles as a "couch potato. If you like to take road trips... I'm your guy! I LOVE car rides. I'm a healthy senior guy with a touch of arthritis, so a home with minimal stairs would be a good fit for me. I do fine in elevators though! I'm a handsome, loving companion who would prefer to be the only animal in your home, unless they're as chill as me. I really hope I don't have to wait too long to find that special someone to share my golden years with. Are you in the market for a snuggly lazy-bones to love on? I'm waiting to meet you!


Note from foster:
Cat compatibility is questionable- he loves to chase squirrels, which are in a similar category
He'd do best in a home without small children as I'm a little ornery at times 

Est. Birthdate: 12/11/2008

If it's love at first sight, head over to the ALIVE website and fill out an application today! https://www.aliverescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
We hope you consider adopting a homeless dog from our shelter or any other shelter in the Mid South area.  All our animals are tested for heartworms, vaccinated, microchipped and most are sterilized prior to adoption.  For more information on any animal listed available for adoption, please call us at 870-732-7599.

Dog Adoption Application 

Thank you for your interest in adopting a pet from West Memphis Animal Services.  We want to place our animals in permanent responsible homes and at the same time match you with a pet that is suitable for your family and your lifestyle.

Our Dog Adoption fee is $100.00 which includes: Current on all shots, Rabies, Spay or Neuter, and testing for heartworms, current heartworm and flea and tick prevention and microchipped.
 **You must be at least 21 years old to apply for adoption. 

Please cut and paste these questions and your answers into a new e-mail and forward them to us at: wmas@westmemphisar.gov
 **If you can't cut and paste this application, you can email us with just the answers to the questions. 

1. Name:
2. Date of Birth: 
3. Spouse or Co-Applicant:
4. Address/City/State/Zip:
5. What area do you live in? 
6. Home Number:
7. Work Number:
8. Cell Number:
9. Email Address:
10. Occupation:
11. Spouse/Co-Applicant Occupation:
12. Are you a student?
13. Name of Pet You Are Applying For:
14. Why are you interested in this pet? 
15. Do you Own or Rent your home? 
16. Please describe your home environment: (Apartment, House, Condo, Townhouse, Trailer, Mobile Home, Pool) 
17. Do you have a pet door? 
18. Do you have a completely fenced in yard? How tall is your fence? 
19. What type of fence do you have (wood, chain link, etc)? 
20. If you do not have a fence, how do you plan to confine the pet to your yard? 
21. If you rent, do you have the landlord's permission to adopt an animal? 
22. Name of Landlord and phone number: 
23. Is there is a pet deposit or fee required? If so, have you paid it? 
24. Does your job require that you move or travel often? 
25. When traveling what do you do with your pet?
26. Number of adults in household? 
27. Do any children live in or visit your home? What are their ages?
28. Please list the names, ages, and breeds of the pets you currently own:
29. Please list the pets you have had in the past and explain what happened to them.
30. Are your pets vaccinated? 
31. Are your pets on heartworm prevention? If so, what brand?
32. Have your pets been spayed or neutered? 
33. If no, please explain.
34. Who is or was your Vet, including address and phone number: 
35. How many times a day do you feed and what brand food do you feed?
36. Please describe what a typical day and a typical week will be for your new pet. 
37. Where will the dog spend its days? 
38. Where will the dog sleep at night? 
39. How many hours a day will the pet be left alone?
40. Do you plan to allow the dog outdoors? 
41. How long do you plan to keep this pet?
42. What behaviors would you consider unacceptable in your pet?
43. How would you correct these behaviors?
44. What would you do if your dog kept having accidents in the house? 
45. How would you discipline your dog from unwanted behavior? 
46. Have you ever kennel trained a dog before? 
47. Are you prepared for the costs involved in properly caring for a pet (food, treats, toys, grooming, shots, heartworm and flea and tick prevention, litter, etc)?
48. Many breeds are now banned in apartments and by insurance companies. If you are applying for a rottweiler, german shepherd, akita, doberman, pitbull, chow, or other guardian type breed, have you checked with your homeowner's insurance to make sure that you are allowed to own the breed? If you are applying to adopt a rottweiler from us, what insurance company are you with?
49. Is the animal going to be a gift for someone?
50. Are other members of your family aware that you want to adopt an animal?
51. Is anyone in your family allergic to animals?
52. Do you have any health issues that could affect your ability to care for a companion pet? 
53. Have you adopted an animal before? If so, where?
54. How did you hear about us? (petfinder, facebook, friend, etc)
55. Do you understand that if you adopt a pet from us, you are required to return the pet to us if you can no longer keep it?
56. The vet reference is usually all we need as a reference, however in some cases we do need to check other references. Please list 2 references, including name and telephone number in case we need to contact them.
57. We very rarely adopt long distance, if you are out of the area, how would you plan to get the pet? 
58. How would you return the pet to us if the pet didn't work out in your home?
59. Please add any comments you would like to make here that will help us make a good decision for you and for your new companion. 

Thank you for your interest in one of our homeless pets! Your answers will be reviewed and your vet reference will be contacted. We will contact you as quickly as we can, but please remember we deal with a high volume of calls, emails, and applications. 

An incomplete application WILL NOT be processed. Falsification of any of the above information will be grounds for rejection of this application.

animal.description:
Jack and Jill are a BONDED PAIR, meaning we are only adopting them out together.  They came to us together and appear to be life-mates.  They were found together after their previous owner dumped them in a park.  Passersby were feeding them hotdogs and they survived on that and garbage for about a month before someone notified us about them.  We agreed to rescue them, and when they were caught, it turned out that Jill was pregnant!  Shortly after rescuing the pair, Jill delivered 3 healthy puppies that look just like her, so we aren't sure if Jack was the father or not.  Since we could not adopt Jill out until after the pups were weaned, we got more time to see Jack and Jill together and realized they are indeed inseparable and love each other very much.

Jack is the white one, and we really have NO idea what breed mix he is, so we took a guess.  But we make no guarantees and could be very wrong!  What we do know is, he is believed to be under 2 years old, and weighs about 15 lbs. and is full grown.  Jack is described by his foster mom ans very sweet and cuddly, but a bit skittish. She is working on teaching him some commands (he knows none), but it scares him.   Jack is mostly housebroken, but will have accidents in the house.  He is a runner and will need a secure fenced yard.  Also, due to his size, he is at risk from birds of prey so he can NEVER be left alone outside unattended.  Jack walks okay on a leash, but not great and will need work on this.  Jack is very quiet and currently does not bark, not even when someone comes to the door.

Jack is fully vetted, heartworm negative, on heartworm and flea prevention, is neutered, and microchipped, and has received a clean bill of health.

Jill's foster mom says Jill is also very sweet, though not as cuddly as Jack. She is fully housebroken and does not have accidents in the house.  Jill is also a runner and will need to be secured outside with a leash or securely fenced yard. 
 She also cannot be left alone outside as she also weighs under 20 lbs and is full grown.  She is estimated to be about the same age as Jack, under 2 years old.  Jill does not like being on a leash and needs to be walked with a harness. Jill is also quiet, but will bark at the foxes in the farm behind the foster's house.  She does not bark at the door.  Jill also lacks basic commands.

Jill's puppies are grown and were adopted, and she has been spayed, heartworm tested negative, on heartworm and flea/tick prevention, and fully vetted and microchipped.  She also received a clean bill of health.

Both Jack and Jill like to sleep under the covers.  A blanket over them is fine.  They are not chewers of furniture, etc., but will dig in the yard if you have moles. 
 Foster mom says, "OMG, will they dig for moles."  This is definitely a terrier trait and cannot really be trained out of them.  However, leaving them alone outside puts them at risk for being snatched by birds of prey, so that will be minimized if they are attended to at all times when outdoors.  Though bonded, when they are asleep, they don’t like the other in their space and will growl.  They have not had any fights though.  They are a very sweet pair, but will need lots of love and some training and socialization.

Adopters must understand that Jack and Jill are ONLY adoptable together, and the adoption fee shown is for BOTH dogs, not individually.  Interested adopters please email MJsAnimalSanctuary@gmail.com to request an adoption application and ask any questions you have.  Older versions of our adoption application you may find online somewhere WILL NOT be accepted, because you will miss important adoption information if you do not email requesting the application.  Phone calls about adoption inquiries WILL NOT be returned, we handled all inquiries via email only.  Prospective adopters are subject to reference check, vet reference, home visit(s), and meet and greet(s) with all human and furry family members living in the home.  Adoption fee is $700 for both Jack and Jill.

If you are ready for a friendly, energetic companion, make an appointment and meet the fantastic Flynn today!

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email US at

m
klumsden1969@gmail.com

You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.

Dog's Name: Gucci

Estimated Breed : Hound Mix

Approximate Age: 3-4 years

Approximate Weight: approx. 35 lbs

Currently Living at: Boarding

Adoption Fee: $300

DOG'S DESCRIPTION

Gucci is a very friendly, handsome fellow who is ready and waiting to find his forever home. He likes people and is excellent with all dogs. Gucci has lots of energy, still quite puppy-like, so he definitely needs a fenced yard where he can run and play. He would love to be part of your pack!

Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.

Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.

Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org

Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!

For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.

Please "like" our
Facebook Page
for the most current events and new dogs.

Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Meet Miskit! Miskit is an approximately 4 year old pit bull mix who is ready for her new home. This poor girl has had four litters. She is now spayed and ready to lead a life of her own.
Miskit LOVES: car trips, toys, people, and belly rubs. She enjoys walks and has good leash manners. She will be your co pilot on life's journeys.
Miskit is full of love to share, She's sweet, loyal and rarely barks. And she is an excellent snuggler!
She's very strong. She should have a strong adult walk her, because a random squirrel can send her galloping down the road.
Mostly happy inside, Miskit doesn't seem to mind being kept in the laundry room when you're not home. She's gentle in the house, with no indication of being destructive. Her happy place is on the couch, close by your side.
It is reported that she is not good with cats so we are looking for a cat free home. She has shown no aggression toward dogs, but we are looking for a home where she would get a lot of one on one.

For the fastest response, please submit an Application so we can help you with a good dog match. Thanks for considering giving a rescue dog a second chance at happiness in a loving home. If a dog is still posted on our website - the dog is still available for adoption. Yolo SPCA is based in Davis, California (near Sacramento). All our dogs are in foster homes (an advantage to adopters because we know the dogs). We do not have a shelter to visit. Because of coronavirus health advisories, our adoption events on Saturdays at Petco are on hold. But, if you submit an application we will arrange for you to meet dogs you are interested in that would be a good match. Our goal is to make the best match possible for the dog and for the human/s. Having our dogs live in foster homes gives us the opportunity to learn about each dog's personality and behavior. We give you as much information as we have about each dog based on our observations or information we've received. We rarely know with certainty the breed or age of our rescue dogs. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out an application at https://form.jotform.com/52017002013129/. Use just one application for any/all of our dogs you are interested in, or instead of the name of one dog, put multiple names or "not sure" on the application. Information on your application helps us know your situation so we can work with you to make a great dog-human match. Our dogs are not adopted on a first-come-first served basis. We are trying to make the best match possible. Yolo SPCA dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, heart worm tested, current on vaccinations, and are being treated with heartworm prevention and flea prevention. Our adoption fees are $175 for each adult dog, $200 for each puppy age 6 months to 1 year old, and $250 for each puppy under 6 months of age. If you have questions, please e-mail (dogs@yolospca.org), and we will do our best to answer your email within 24 to 48 business hours. Donating to Yolo SPCA, or shopping at our SPCA Thrift Store supports our rescue efforts (http://yolospca.org/about-our-thrift-store/). Yolo County SPCA is always looking for foster homes, volunteers (http://yolospca.org/volunteer/), and donations (http://yolospca.org/donate/). Thank you.Apply to adopt here! Online cat application form
Please expect up to 3-5 business days to hear back once you have submitted an application.
The Yolo County SPCA is a nonprofit foster home based organization located in Yolo County California.

All of our felines have been spayed/neutered, microchipped, FeLV tested, and vaccinated prior to adoption. Kittens have received at least one FVRCP and adults are up-to-date on vaccines. The fee to adopt is $90 for kittens ($135 for a pair) or $60 for adult cats over 1 year ($90 for a pair).
For more information about an animal, please email yolospcafoster@gmail.com. For more general questions, please see our website at www.yolospca.org.

animal.description:
Introducing Cindy!

Cindy is a shy Beagle mix girl who is as sweet as they come. It takes her a little while to warm up to you but it's worth the wait. We are pretty sure she is potty trained and with slow introductions, she is good with other dogs. (She and another of our dogs, Cindy are both shy but absolutely LOVE each other so much, we feel they would both florish if adopted together. They are both small and no trouble at all). animal.description:
Meet Chevy Chevy, an eight-year-old hound mix who identifies completely with Oscar the Grouch. Chevy is also a volunteer favorite and very hard not to spoil. 

Chevy is anxious and fearful. He takes medication but what he really needs is a home where his person will let him take his time opening up. He will need a crate to relax in but once he warms up, he will be a couch sitting, Netflix binging champion. 

Chevy is house broken if he has a fenced in yard. Kind of like those people who don't like to go to public bathrooms- they'd rather do their business at home. 

Chevy would do best with a single person, with no children. This person would have to be open to the required training that would help him adjust to his new home. Chevy really responds well to training games with jerky treats. 

Chevy is an amazing dog who hasn't been given the time to decompress and see what home life is all about. He deserves a home with a person who will make him feel safe and loved. In return, he will be the sweetest, goofiest, most grateful pup!

animal.description: Bubba came in with his two sisters when they were not able to find homes for these three. He is the most skiddish of the three that came in, and takes the longest to warm up to us. Bubba just wasn't socialized up to this point so he doesn't realize that other humans, animals, new places, etc. are not going to hurt him. We are working to get him out of his shell, but it is taking some more time with him. Bubba is rather unsure about our treats and attention yet, but he is starting to come around to the fact that we're not so bad. Due to him being in quarantine for vaccinations, we have not had the chance to introduce him to other animals, but he does not seem to mind our clinic cats that we have. Once Bubba warms up to you, he's going to want to be with you all the time, you will become his comfort zone and will be able to show him that life isn't so bad. He needs someone who will be patient with him and let him do things at his own pace. Bubba is up to date on vaccines and will be neutered before leaving. If you would like to be Bubba's forever home please contact us at pcanimalshelter@live.com or 308-352-2630.

animal.description: Stella: She is a great girl. She enjoys sleeping on her bed and blanket. She sometimes snores. Jen the dog groomer reported that Stella was a good girl for her bath and manicure. Stella did so well when given her heartworm and flea prevention as well. She is a bit of a queen when it comes to her food. I found using 2cups dry and a half a cup canned food will work. Also, the food and water need to be placed in close proximity where she will sleep. She loves female humans better than male. When there is much stimulus, she will shake a bit and become very observant and would like to be somewhere quieter. She has had zero accidence in the house and enjoys the outside. She is very loyal, protective and loving to the one who treats her the best and the longest. I believe she will do that with any female forever home. She can stay alone in the house for 8 hours and you will never need to worry about anything being destroyed. She doesn't do treats, toys or fetch however, she will play with you. She likes pets, belly rubs and butt scratches. She does not mind cats at all if the cat likes her. She will cower to a cat who is dominant. She did not do well at the shelter. Stella has been a blessing to watch bloom into a girl's best friend. Finding her forever home is essential.

animal.description:
$100 of adoption fee Sponsored$100 of Freckles adoption fee is Sponsored. Freckles should change her name to George Lopez because she is the definition of a "low rider." All jokes aside, this girl is SUCH a cutie. She has the shortest legs and has quite a bit of junk in the trunk and we couldn't love her any more than we do. Freckles is a momma dog who came to us from Arkansas, where she was in an animal control facility who was running out of space to keep her. They reached out to us to see if we could welcome her and her litter of puppies, and of course we said yes! Freckles is a very sweet girl with all people and would likely be great with kids based off of her sweet and loving personality.

Freckles did not test well with cats, so a home without them is a must! She tested well with a submissive male dog, but once sharing attention was on the table, she became very reactive, so a home where she is the only pet may be the best "forever" fit for this little butterball turkey.

Freckles is 3 years old. Her adoption fee is $185, and she is spayed, microchipped and current on all vaccines. Apply online for Freckles today!

If you are interested in adopting please go to our website at www.partnersforpetsil.org and fill out an online application.

Adoptions are held at the O'Fallon, IL PetSmart every Saturday of the month from 11am-3:30pm and at the Glen Carbon, IL PetSmart every Sunday from 11am-3:30pm. We are also at Petco in Edwardsville Crossing on Sundays from 11:30-3:30 pm. The cats are only at Glen Carbon Petsmart. Please let us know if you are interested in a pet and we can arrange to have them meet you at one of the adoption events.

Introducing Bandit!

Bandit is a 3 yr old low rider who weights 53 lbs. Sadly, he was owner surrendered by his owner due to health problems. His owner simply couldn't care for him anymore. (Please no negative comments as this was very hard on the owner). With the help of many caring people, we were able to save him from the shelter. He is doing well with his foster (who is new to fostering). Bandit LOVES playing with toys. He also loves tug of war with ropes and fetching balls. His best home would be with an individual, couple, or family who has plenty of time for him. He definitely loves interaction with people. He wants to please and make his humans happy. 

He had to learn to walk on a leash in addition to go up stairs. It only took him a few times as soon as he saw it pleased his foster.

Bandit is current on his vaccinations and is heartworm negative. He has an appt to be neutered and microchipped soon. 

Bandit's best fit would be a home where he is the only pet. He doesn't do well with other dogs. And although we haven't had him around cats, we wouldn't recommend them either. 

If you feel as though Bandit would be a good fit for you and your family, please complete the following Adoption agreement. He is a great dog who deserves a loving family.

animal.description:
Have you met Carlton?

9-year-old Mikey and his brother Carlton were rescued from Barstow Humane Society in June by Holly's Garden Rescue and then transferred to us on November 19th for help in socializing them. While they were in the care of Holly's Garden Rescue, Mikey and Carlton were examined by a vet, and both had dental surgery. Both boys weighs 8 lbs.

When Mikey (folded ears) and Carlton (pointy ears) first came to FFF, they were terrified with a capital T! We had them drag leashes in the play yard so we could catch them and double leashed them when bringing them out on walks just in case. We sent them out on a two-week Frosted Fling which turned into a foster, and wow, these boys have come a long way!

Mikey and Carlton lived with another small dog and a cat and got along well with everyone! They seem to be potty pad trained, but their Flingers are working on getting them to potty outside. It's clear that the boys haven't spent much time on leash, so the first step was getting them used to being leashed. Now that they are more comfortable, their Fling Fam is able to walk them out to the yard for potty breaks. Mikey and Carlton are big foodies and can easily be won over with food. Roasted chicken is a favorite of the boys and their Flingers use it to get the boys more comfortable to new things. Mikey is the more confident of the two. He settled in more quickly and will follow his Flingers and settle in next to them on the couch. Carlton follows his brother's lead, but is much more reserved. He has taken his time to get used to his Fling Fam, but is still timid and prefers to spend time in his safe crate when he gets overwhelmed.

Their Fling Fam told us, "Mikey is definitely the more confident one and Carlton takes his lead. They now hang out on the couch more than their crate! Treats have played a big part in starting to get these guys more comfortable on a leash. For the most part I take them outside for potty breaks, but if they need to go they will use the wee wee pad by the door. They do the cutest little dances when it is time to eat!

Mikey and Carlton will need a very patient family. These guys have come a long way, but they still have a way to go in order to be their happiest selves. Apply to bring them home at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

animal.description:
Pet Name:  Miles * PS 
Breed(s): Cane Corso 
Color(s):  Black
Gender: Male 
Est. Age: 4-5 yrs old 
Est Weight: over 100 pounds 
Energy Level: Moderate 

Apartment:  No 
House trained: Yes 
Crate trained: Yes
Microchipped: Yes 
Spay / Neutered: Yes 
Current Vaccinations: Yes 
Training: Working on obedience, has good house manners 
Dog-friendly: Yes 
Cat-friendly: No 
Kid-friendly: Yes

Miles has a story. We do not know what this big guy has been through, but we know it was rough.  Miles showed up at our property at 4 am in 27 degrees. Very emaciated, cold, covered in cactus, scared, confused, and face swollen with infection.  He could not smell right because of his swollen face or see out of his left eye. Thankfully our dogs let us know he was sitting at the gate asking for help! 

We immediately opened the gate, and then he slowly & cautiously came in. It took about an hour for him to trust us enough to come inside the house. Once he arrived in warmed up & had a bit of food, he allowed us to remove all the cactus he had in his body & legs. Given Sub Q fluids to get him through until we could get him to our vet the next morning. 

After seeing our vet, who loves this big adorable guy, he was prescribed antibiotics for 10 days & sub Q fluids for 4 days. He only weighed 96 pounds. Heartbreaking, this magnificent dog was beaten down and mistreated terribly. 
While we have no idea who dumped this big loving boy, we know he went through abusive treatment and starved. He had looked like he had been through a dogfight, because of the injuries & swelling to his face, but definitely starved.  
Even though this big guy went through this horrible treatment, he is very loving & forgiving. 

Miles is doing better in just a little over 2 weeks. His energy is up. He is holding weight & still gaining what he needs to become a healthy dog. 

He enjoys being with the other dogs daily & just lounging around the house. 

He does very well with other nondominant, properly trained, and socialized dogs of all sizes. We did find out that, unfortunately for cats, they do seem to be on his menu. No cats with this big guy. 
Because of his condition, Miles has been traveling with us everywhere we go. This is more than most new dogs we take in. His horrible condition is only because of neglect & abuse. He has been going with us to do donation pick-ups & our fundraisers. H LOVES car rides, and he is well behaved too. 

Miles is looking for a family that has experience owning mastiff breeds. 

Cane Corso's are a very different & special breed. They are loyal protectors of their families. And like Miles, some love to cuddle & are very affectionate with humans. 

Miles is on the right path now. If you are looking for a big loving dog to join in on family adventure and fun, or cuddle with at night while watching a movie, Miles might be your guy! 

We would love for someone whose lifestyle can work with Mile's needs and healing to bring him home while still getting healthy.  
Perfect bonding time for Miles & the family.
Once the vet medically clears him, we will neuter him, he will be a foster to adopt agreement. 

Adoption donation fee and home inspection required. 
Application for adopting and fostering -   https://form.jotform.com/201328449376157

Thank you, 
Dharma DOG Movement
Awareness | Advocacy | Saving Lives

If you have any questions about fostering or adopting, please contact Dharma Dog Movement directly at adopt@dharmadogmovement.org

11/2020

animal.description:
I object!...An adorable puppy like me should definitely have a forever home by now. My name is Lawyer and I am a 22 pound Boxer mix boy. I was born in mid-August, so I'm still just a puppy with lots of energy and have lots of growing to do, so will need a fully privacy fenced yard in which to run and play (no apartment life for me). I get along great with other dogs and love children. I am still in puppy school, but am so close to earning my degrees in house training and kennel training. I have worked hard on my L"Sits", and have mastered that command with flying colors, and am also working on learning all sorts of other useful things. Well, ladies and gentlemen, I rest my case on why I am the perfect new addition for your family!


I am currently enrolled in the Pups 4 Parole training program, learning all of the things I need to know to make me a great family member. I need someone willing to keep up my training so that I don't forget everything I am learning.


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
If I were to sing a song about Taco it would be "I'm just a lonely boy, lonely and blue, I'm all alone, with nothing to do".... Poor Taco. It's not his fault that he's all alone. His owner has been separated from him due to personal circumstances and he's been left alone except for those visits when his owner comes to feed him. I'm not here to judge only to try to help his owner find him a new home. 

His owner tells me that Taco is a loving boy and has never shown any type of aggression towards a human. He keeping him company for the time being, but he isn't fond of other dogs  in general. He's a dog that will bond to a human in a one pet household, he being the only pet. 

He's not a very active fellow, quite laid back. He's 8 years of age and at his stage of life is quite happy as a couch potato, though he also might enjoy walks. This is a complimentary listing for this dog in hopes that he will have a chance to live out the remainder of his life in a loving home. If that might happen to be you, please email me with a few details about yourself and I will put you in touch with Taco's owners.

animal.description:
MEET RANDALL!!

Randall is a happy, 4 yr old handsome boy! Randall loves to go for a walks. He likes to pull a bit on his walk because he is ready to go!! He could benefit from some continued leash training. He knows how to sit for treats, takes them gently. He is VERY treat motivated and is easy to train new commands.

Randall deserves a home of his own. A home where he is the only dog and doesn't have to compete for attention with any children. He just wants all the attention to himself. If you like to play fetch and tug-o-war, then Randall is the guy for you. After some play time, he would love nothing more than to curl up next to you for a nap. He is a little skittish of loud noises and can be startled easily. He barks when meeting someone new, but he quickly warms up to them especially if they play with him. And if you come bearing treats, he will gently take them from you and shower you with love.

Do you want to run, walk, or hike with Randall? Then, he is the perfect pup for you!

If you are interested in adopting Randall, please visit our website for our application www.underdogaz.com

animal.description:
Pet Name: Niko * SD 
Breed(s): Siberian Husky 
Color(s): Red Piebald 
Gender: male 
Est. Age: 4yrs old 
Est Weight: 60 Pounds 
Energy Level: moderate 

Apartment:  No 
House trained: Yes 
Crate trained: Hates Crates / not needed 
Microchipped: Yes 
Spay / Neutered: Yes 
Current Vaccinations: Yes 
Training: Working on obedience, good house manners 
Dog-friendly: yes 
Cat-friendly: yes 
Kid-friendly: yes

Niko is a fun and loving, happy boy looking for an active experienced husky family. He would love to do daily runs or go on lots of hiking adventures! He is a Flashy Beautiful boy, but his coat comes with a lot of work. 

He is a wooly coat, meaning it is thicker & longer than the average standard Siberian coat. 

Niko is a social butterfly that has been getting along with almost every dog he meets! And he adores cats. He gets a little excited & tries to mount, so he must be introduced appropriately & corrected to avoid this behavior. We are currently working on this daily as he hangs out with about 10 other dogs of all sizes here at our rescue. 

We do not recommend dog parks. Although a social butterfly, Niko still has to work on boundaries & manners with other dogs. Niko prefers and needs colder weather. He insists on sleeping outside at night when it is the coldest. Then in the house with family during the day. He is a velcro dog and wants to be right by your side. If you think your lifestyle will work with Nikos's needs & you are looking for an active adventure buddy, he is taking applications!

Adoption donation fee and home inspection required. 
Application for adopting and fostering -   https://form.jotform.com/201328449376157

animal.description:
Konan von Kothen is a stunning 2 year old black and red German Shepherd.  Konan's  early demeanor with us communicates quiet reserve, caution, and surveillance – all attributes needed to assess his environment properly. Konan is seeking a calm and experienced adult home. He tends to keep to himself and observe, and needs time to get to know new people. With time and training and bonding, Konan will become more secure and reveal more of himself. He just needs his person to continue to help him build trust and cement  the connections he so richly deserves. Konan seems more uneasy with men (he can bark at men he doesn't know), so proper introductions are required, and will only solidify his faith in himself and his forever family. He is okay around other dogs at the rescue, mostly just observing and  keeping to himself. Konan is a classically handsome Shepherd just waiting for his forever person to unlock all his mightiness.
 No cats please!

Westside dog Biographies, availability and new photos are updated regularly on our website! So, check in and log on often! 

Westside thanks you for looking at our amazing dogs and for choosing to save an animal's life through rescue. 

Don't forget to visit your local animal shelter...the source of many of our dogs.
 
www.sheprescue.org

https://www.facebook.com/WGSRescue

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Bronson, and I am as sweet as I am big!  I am a pretty big boy and very strong but I am quick to learn when to be gentle. I already know sit and shake and am ready to learn anything you want to teach me! I love to go for a walk, and am pretty good on a leash (getting better daily!). I am eager to please and am good with other dogs I have met. I am too interested in kitties, but a home with medium to large dogs sounds great! I am ready to find an active forever family who will love me for my beauty and brains!  I really am a very, very nice boy. 

ADOPTION FEE: $200 (All MVPC dogs are heartworm-tested, completely vetted, spayed/neutered, microchipped, crate-trained and house-trained)

A $100 hold fee is required for approved applications and will be applied to the full adoption fee at the time of the home visit. 
ADOPTER: Dog experience
BIRTHDAY: Estimated 1 year
FENCE: Required (an electric fence is not an acceptable form of containment)
DOGS: Yes
CATS: No
CHILDREN: Yes, 5 and over simply because I am big and strong.

INQUIRIES: ALL inquiries begin with a submitted adoption application, which is found on our website, www.miamivalleypitcrew.com. We do not adopt to individuals under the age of 25. We prefer male/female dog pairings unless both already reside in the home. 

DO NOT: USE THE PETFINDER CONTACT/ADOPT BUTTONS--we are unable to monitor those and you will not receive a response. 

PLEASE NOTE: We are volunteer based and a home visit is required; we have a two-hour adoption radius from Kettering, OH for our adult dogs and 75 miles for our puppies. Exceptions for our ADULT dogs only, though rare, may be made on a case-by-case basis but we must be able to do a home visit. Thank you for your understanding!

Professional holiday and Valentine’s Day pictures courtesy of the talented Gwen Estep Photography, LLC https://www.facebook.com/GwenEstepPhotography/

animal.description:
Animal Profile:
Conan is an estimated 3 year old 63 lb German Shepherd Dog who joined us from California on September 13th. We will post more information as we get to know him.

Seattle Foster Update: Conan is settling in well. He's a young, energetic dog who loves to play but has also learned an off switch inside the home. Conan is non-reactive to other dogs on leash and has been in previous homes with other dogs but he really prefers to be the main center of attention and we would like to place him in a home without other dogs. Conan is house trained and crate trained and has made incredible improvements on leash and no longer pulls. It takes him a little to warm up so slow introductions will be beneficial but once he's used to you, he's a total love bug and is becoming more and more friendly with the neighbors and less wary of strangers.

We are looking at placing Conan in an active home familiar with his breed, some patience, and willingness to continue to work with him. We recommend a home without small children and a yard to run in. While he has been in a home with a cat, he did chase the cat so we are looking for a cat free home.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue. Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Morgan von Mosbach is a wonderful 8-9-year-old smaller-sized, frosty-faced Shepherd mix.  This good boy has it all – the wonderful GSD traits we all know and love, PLUS plenty of experience in good doggy behavior!  Morgan is an easy-going dog who just wants to hang out with his people.  He walks wonderfully on leash – he never pulls while he strolls by your side.  He’s quick to ask for affection by leaning into you, and he’s always thrilled to be wherever you happen to be.  Morgan does a marvelous job in playgroup – he has a great medium level of energy and likes exploring and meeting other dogs (he’ll avoid the pushy pups – smart guy! And, he's a no for cats.) If you’re looking for a dog with tons of good boy experience, Morgan is the pup you’ve been waiting for!

Westside dog Biographies, availability and new photos are updated regularly on our website! So, check in and log on often!

animal.description:
Gender: Male
Breed/s: Pit Bull Mix
Approximate Age: 3 yrs
Approximate Weight/Size: Approx. 65lbs
Good with: People,  Dogs but not cats
Not tested with: Hobbits and Ninjas
Fully Vaccinated: Yes
Neutered: Yes
Microchipped: Yes
House Trained: Yes
Crate/Kennel Trained: Yes
Important Notes: Stray Rescue

Chance came to WTWTA Rescue after we were notified about a stray pitbull dragging a 20 ft chain up and down the country side. Thank fully those good samaritans didn’t just watch the dog suffer they jumped in and start working with this pup to get him to trust them by feeding him. Food is love right!?

They started calling him Chance after the name of the pitbull pup in homeward bound movie who had a very similar eye patch. Chance was at first a little untrusting of humans but these folks have turn things around for him. He does amazing with other dogs and small children. He lives with his foster family who has both. He likes car rides and knows several commands, sit, down, up and even hugs….

Chance had been running around loose for awhile, left to suffer on a chain by his neglectful past owner, he was once a visitor at the Augusta shelter. They released him back to the owner who then just tied him up again. The owner since disappeared leaving Chance on a chain to suffer and starve. But his spirit still had some fight left in him and he broke the chain free and ran to find a place where he could be loved. 

Chance will need a patient and loving owner who will understand his rough past and go slow with him to ensure he knows he can trust them. But once that trust is built, this boy loves hard and he is faithful beyond words.

As big as he is, he is just a sweet lapdog who loves snuggling on top of his person and watching tv and talking about all the cool things he saw outside for the day. 


If you are interested in Chance, please make a note in your adoption application

www.wherethewildthingsarerescue.com
Adoption Fee is $300

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email jessalynL@k-9lifesavers.org
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: Alice
Estimated Breed : Bulldog Mix
Approximate Age: 1 year
Approximate Weight: approx. 54 lbs
Currently Living at: Foster
Adoption Fee: $300
DOG'S DESCRIPTION
Alice is a sweet tripod hoping to find her forever home. She is very friendly and loving, especially during bath time! She is pretty mellow, and can't walk super long distances, but she is the perfect companion dog. She is picky about her dog friends (and wouldn't do well with cats), but loves people, especially men. She loves car rides and snuggles. Can you find some room in your home and heart for this special lady? Alice would prefer to find a home with children over 10 years old as she likes her space and gets defensive when the tiny ones invade her space.
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Please "like" our Facebook Page for the most current events and new dogs.
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Bunny’s owners  neglected her and then refused to pick her up at the shelter where she was turned in as a stray.  While Bunny was shaking in fear at the shelter, she quickly acclimated to her foster home where she feels safe and is fostered with other dogs. We know her prior owner had children and while in foster, she has welcomed affection from visiting children.   Bunny’s foster says she’s super friendly and snuggly, and is very quiet and doesn’t bark much and is doing great with the other dogs, but she gets along best with calm dogs.  Bunny does needs to be fed in a separate area from other dogs, as she has shown some food guarding behavior  (a little growling when the food is put).  She enjoys snatching house slippers and running around the house with them.  She likes to be right next to you or in the same room and loves tossing and playing with toys, and will always jump up to greet you. She loves to lick your ankles and calves when she's following you around,  and she loves to rest her head on your heart.

While she can be mouthy when playing or hyper excited, she does not bite hard. She also gets excited licking her human and licks will escalate to big, toothy opened mouth kisses but she is gentle. Bunny can be territorial of her human's lap when other dogs come around, so she needs an adopter who will reinforce the boundaries her foster is setting. Bunny is mostly potty trained but does have a habit of pooping on shaggy bathroom rugs, but not on regular carpeting. Bunny was forced to live outside her whole life, so a little confusion is to be expected.   

Poor Bunny has heartworms and we are treating her skin issue (not contagious).  Both of these conditions come from being neglected so we are grateful that she is now in our care so she can receive medical treatment.  Bunny’s fur is already growing back and she can continue her Heartworm Treatment in her adopter’s home, which is sponsored by New Hope Animal Rescue. 

Bunny 
Female 
Chihuahua mix 
Age 2 
10lbs

Due to the high volume of emails we receive, if you are seriously interested in Bunny, the best first step is completing our adoption application.  You then will be offered an opportunity to speak to her foster to get to know her in more detail and if you think it's a good fit, we would arrange a meet and greet. 
 
https://nhanimalrescue.org/adoption-information/

animal.description:
Oh gosh, how cute is Francis??  This little guy is around 2-3 years old, and was surrendered to a rural shelter to be euthanized as his owner did not want to deal with his Infrequent seizures.  Luckily, the shelter staff thought they could do better and immediately posted him and sent out emails, which is where we stepped in.  Heelers are a director favorite!

Francis is good with kids over eight (due to breed herding instincts) and other dogs.  He’d prefer maybe just one or two playmates, not a houseful.  He’s great on car rides, end enjoys walks and playing ball.

We are looking for someone comfortable with handling and medicating Francis should he have a seizure, ideally within easy driving range of Guardian Vet in Brewster, NY.  

Please use our fillable app to apply to foster or foster to adopt here:  https://forms.gle/eqEChRtYMPshWYuX8

animal.description:
Fozzie was turned into a rural kill shelter as a stray. He was found extremely under weight with an imbedded collar around his neck and chain wrapped tightly around his torso. He had a ripped ear and was missing fur (growing back!), which comes with being neglected and forced to live outside. Yet amazingly, Fozzie is the sweetest dog! Fozzie loves affection and loves being near his human. He loves other dogs and is learning how to to be around cats. He enjoys good chew toys and his foster says he’s very smart and trainable. An owner with an active lifestyle who is down to snuggle would be ideal for Fozzie. The foster describes his energy level as moderate to high.  Fozzie is a big, lovable puppy and will need someone who is willing to invest time to train him but his foster is working on some basic commands.  He is adjusting to sleeping in his crate at night.  While he’s only 45lbs right now, he is under weight. 

Fozzie 
Male 
Shepherd Mix/Yellow Lab Mix 
1 1/2 years 
45 lbs

Due to the high volume of emails we receive, if you are seriously interested in Fozzie, the best first step is completing our adoption application.  You then will be offered an opportunity to speak to his foster to get to know him in more detail and if you like what you hear, we would arrange a meet and greet.

animal.description:
$125 of adoption fee sponsoredIf Nixie were a fruit, why, she'd be a Georgia peach because this little girl is just as sweet as pie. She is roughly 4 years old, 55 pounds of pure, unconditional love. She just wants to be next to her person at all times. One quick look at her adorable pittie belly and you can tell Nixie has clearly mothered multiple litters of puppies. Her little triangle ears sit perched on top of her head in the cutest way imaginable. We don't know exactly what her life was like before finding her way to Partners for Pets, but we know for sure that her days of litter after litter are in the past and she can finally live her life as a loved family pet. Nixie would fit best in a home without cats. She is currently working on her socialization and how to be friends with other dogs, but for right now, she would fit best as an only dog. Her adoption fee is $195, which includes her spay, microchip and up-to-date vaccines! Wont you come meet her at the shelter? She's waiting for you!

If you are interested in adopting please go to our website at www.partnersforpetsil.org and fill out an online application.

Adoptions are held at the O'Fallon, IL PetSmart every Saturday of the month from 11am-3:30pm and at the Glen Carbon, IL PetSmart every Sunday from 11am-3:30pm. We are also at Petco in Edwardsville Crossing on Sundays from 11:30-3:30 pm. The cats are only at Glen Carbon Petsmart. Please let us know if you are interested in a pet and we can arrange to have them meet you at one of the adoption events.

animal.description:
I am Portia, I came from a puppy mill where my job for all 6 years of my life has been making babies. Unfortunately, that means all my calcium supply when not making the babies was making milk for the babies so there was not any left to keep my teeth healthy. I had my spay and dental when I came into rescue and ended up only getting to keep 1 tooth, all the rest were rotten or had already fallen out.
I am learning from the other dogs in my foster home all about being a pet. I am learning to go outside to potty in the yard, that is some weird stuff that green stuff called grass. I am learning to get petted by humans and play with the other dogs.
The dog part is not so bad, but that human part is odd as well. I have never had much good interaction with humans. I will learn though and when I am ready to go to a home I for sure will need a buddy in the home of at least 1 other dog. I will also need a fenced in yard so I can run and play. After all I deserve that since I have been in a cage for 6 years.
If you think I might be a dog you are interested in when I am ready, let us know and we can figure out a way to meet up and check each other out.


All of our dogs are current on vaccinations which include Rabies and Distemper/Parvo, they are spayed and or neutered, have been fecal tested and heartworm tested, and had a dental cleaning if necessary. They are all on heartworm and flea/tick preventative as needed in rescue.

The adoption process is an application, a vet reference, a home inspection, and a lifetime contract. The requested adoption donation for all of our dogs is $300.

We do not REQUIRE a fenced in yard (some dogs do not require a fence, as long as they can walk well on harness and leash. This is decided by what is best for each dog individually.) 

We are willing to adopt out-of-state applicants but you must travel to the Omaha area to meet and travel home with your dog. We do not transport or ship dogs. 

If you are interested in adding this beautiful baby to your loving family, please visit our website and fill out an adoption application at http://www.nebraskadachshundrescue.org/adoptapp.htm 
The Adoption fee is $300.

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Blue Bell. Thank you so much for stopping in to see me. I am a 5 year old pittie mix with my best years still ahead. They found me abandoned by some storage units over 2 years ago which was a very lucky day for me. I went into foster care where I was treated for heartworm, given lots of TLC. 
I am a bit of a chubby gal at 78 pounds but this is covid.... Who here hasn't gained a few? Am I right? My favorite thing is to play with the hose and catch the water in my mouth. I like kids but because I am so big it would be best if kids were 12 and over. I am house trained, crate trained, and leash trained. My foster dad will tell you that i am friendly, playful, and sweet. And, most of all, I love attention. I get along with other dogs but because of my size, my roughhousing can be a little too rough. It is probably best if I am the only dog. I also try to play with kitties but this is a David and Goliath situation and those kitties don't have stones so no kitties please.
ok. Time to get real with you. Nobody knows what happened to me before I was rescued. I am generally sweet and lovable with people but sometimes I get afraid around men. I try to act tough but really I'm just a scared little puppy. When I am frightened and acting out in fear, I need people to remember that i am a little dog at heart who doesn't know she's a big dog and that everyone should treat me gently. I'm a big girl but if you adopted me, I would be your baby. 
I have had my spay and I am up-to-date on vaccines. I am on heartworm preventative and flea& tick preventative. I am looking for a special family with love, and patience and that all important garden hose. If you have a hose and you need a dog to spray, consider me, Blue Bell! If you want to learn more about me and possibly adopt me, contact Alyson (include phone number) at alysonbrunelli@gmail.com and she will walk you through the adoption process. My adoption  fee is $325.
Like us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/pawsclawsnewengland

Follow/tag us on Instagram: @pawsclawsne or #pawsclawsne

animal.description:
Precious Roxy has been in our Gwinnett Jail Dogs Program for several years, waiting patiently as other dogs get chosen every week and she is still left behind. We know her perfect family is out there. Please share this post and help us find them! 

Earlier this week, Roxy enjoyed a day away from the detention facility at our new SOHF Adoption Center. She loved being spoiled by our volunteers and clinic staff while she was there.  Roxy is a large Lab/Pit mix senior girl who is around 9 years old. She needs a home where she would be your one and only pet. She loves humans but she isn’t a fan of other furry creatures. 

Roxy is such a sweet girl! She loves every person she comes into contact with and we don’t want the jail to be her last place she calls home. Roxy does have some medical issues that are common to senior dogs that our vet staff keep a close eye on. We are happy to explain more to anyone seriously interested in providing Roxy a loving retirement home.

*************************************************

Roxy is a recruit in Operation Second Chance, also known as the Gwinnett Jaildog Program. This great program saves shelter dogs from euthanasia, placing them with inmates at the county jail who have been approved to train and nurture them so that they will be good pets in their permanent adoptive homes. The goal is for each dog to be leash trained, housebroken, and have knowledge of basic obedience commands. The dogs also receive some agility training.

Roxy is fully vetted -- spayed/neutered, heartworm negative, and current on vaccinations and deworming.  The adoption fee is $250 (cash only, please).

You can apply to adopt by submitting an application at www.jaildogs.org. Someone will be in touch within 48 hours. You can check the status of your application by emailing jaildogs@gmail.com. 

Get more info about the Gwinnett Jaildog Program at www.jaildogs.org.

animal.description:
Hello! My previous guardians were kicked out of their house by the evil landlord which left me and my best buddy Poppy with nowhere to go. The day we were both supposed to be dumped at the pound, a girl and her mother took us in for foster. Don’t let my size intimidate you because I really am a big silly sweet guy who just wants someone to love. I will bark at strangers at first but get real friendly once I know they're okay. I love treats and food of all kinds, and hugs, tummy rubs and kisses make me so happy. I used to have a slight limp due to a ligament injury in my left hind leg but my foster mom gave me joint supplements and CBD, and I am so much better! I really do enjoy going on short walks. Most of the time, I just enjoy laying around or by your feet. I will sleep on a dog bed next to your bed, love you, protect you, and forever be loyal to you.

If you are interested in meeting this pooch, please download the Adoption Questionnaire (farescue.org/pdf_files/questionnaire_canine.pdf), fill it out and email it back to us at info@farescue.org or fax (310) 362-0321. You can also meet this and/or other available dogs at our weekend adoptions.

[Romeo is 6 years old and weighs 83 lbs.]

(2011)

animal.description:
I'm a 1 year old, 54 Lb, handsome red Husky. I'm a tall, lanky, goofy happy, affectionate guy who loves people and dogs alike. From my foster mom..

Hi my name is Banksy I am the bestess boy looking for my forever home. I have lots of love and cuddles and kisses to spare. I'm a young buck and love to learn new things. I'm told I pick up tricks & behaviors fast especially when hotdogs and cheese are involved!. I definitely love my walks and I'm good on leash. I'm medium energy in the house as long as I've had a couple good walks a day and some play time with my dogmates. I play well with the other dogs in the house,  I love my foster fur siblings. and would love to have a home with another young, playful dog to keep me company and show me the ropes. I'm a lap dog by the way, I'll just sit my fuzzy butt right down on you any chance I get but my favorite thing is to be with my people. I like to crawl into bed like a clumsy fawn to wake you up in the mornings cause I'm soooo excited by the new day ahead and all the things we are going to do together!. My tongue can barely fit in my mouth so it flops out the side often like the derp I am, it makes my foster mom giggle. I like to make her laugh. I have the cutest of extra toes on my back feetsies, for extra grip. I am fully housebroken, yay! Yeah I'm a smart boy.  those hotdogs are my favorite treats and I love all snacks especially frozen carrots and frozen yogurt kongs -nomnom. I guess I bring out the best in dogs. I was told the old lady pupper of the house who's 12 wouldn't play with me but I must have all the right moves because it's no problem getting her to play. I'm great in the car, would make a perfect running and hiking  buddy. I'm looking for an active home, someone who will put up with my big puppy ways and give me the love I'm craving. We are 100% volunteer run rescue and don't have the time to write everyone back so please take the time to fill out an application. We will get back if you seem like the right fit for Banksy. Thank you for understanding. https://www.welcomehomesanctuary.org/

Once dogs in the ORANGE category are comfortable, they will most likely be energetic and needing similar guidance to dogs that are in the YELLOW category. Dogs in the ORANGE category sometimes benefit from another confident canine in the home.

Dogs are assigned to color categories using any previous owner notes, general handling, as well as staff and volunteer observations. As we continue to get to know the dogs and gather further insights into their personalities, colors may be adjusted accordingly.

animal.description:
Yes, Sarah Jessica Barker is back, but to no fault of her own. She is just too obsessed with small animals. 

Upon returning to the Shelter, there is a possibility that Jessica Barker may have an Auto-Immune Disease called Evans Syndrome. She is only currently on medication that she may need for 6 months or for the rest of her life.

With her condition, sadly she will be overlooked time and time again because chronic issues can be pretty scary to some people. But she will repay your kindness with kiss, snuggles, and entertaining moments.

Sarah Jessica Barker is only a year old, filled with energy and ecstatic charm. She will get the zoomies if you run around the yard with her. Her only crutch personality wise will be she cannot be around small animals.

This holiday season, if you wish to give to someone, consider giving this sweetheart a forever home. It takes a community to make a difference. Let's start by changing her life forever.

animal.description:
Welcome Tatum to CCPAL Rescue.  She is a 2.5-year-old American Bulldog mix is our best guess.  She may have some Pittie.  She wears a big smile on her face when she meets new people.  She looks to you for direction and loves being touched and cuddled.  She is a really sweet dog and could go to a family with children.  We think due to her enthusiasm they should be 10 or older.  She has bursts of energy and then is ready chill out and lay down.  She would be a great companion for a more active family.  A fenced yard would be nice.  She could do her exercising in the yard and then be ready to relax inside by your feet while you read.  She weighs about 50 pounds.  Looks like she has had some litters of puppies.  We will spay her and she will probably fill out in her body so her head matches with her body.  She is currently in Texas and can be adopted locally or we can work with one of the local transporters to get her to Washington, Portland, Minnesota, Wisconsin, Vermont or all along the East Coast.  Her adoption fee is 250 and transport is 185.   Rhode Island and Massachusetts are not states we adopt to because of the regulations imposed by these states. 
 
Contact Marlene at 210-867-1769 or email to ccpalinquiries@gmail.com if you have questions.  Online applications at www.ccpal.info/  See her cute video!!

animal.description:
****PETronus Rescue endeavors to include all pertinent information for each of the dogs within our organization with regard to approximate age, potty training status, kennel training status, temperament, activity level, dog/cat friendliness, etc in an effort to give those considering adopting as much information as we have.  Inquiries requesting additional information will not be returned, due to limited volunteers. Thank you for your understanding **** 

Meet Baloo.

Baloo came to us from one of our local shelters, where he was on the euthanasia list. He is estimated to be about 2 years old and LOVES people. 

Baloo needs to be the only animal in the home but is 100% about people and loves with his whole heart.

He is not a dog park dog, but enjoys yard time with his human and walks/ runs as well! 

If you are looking to add a dog to your family who is all about people, Baloo is the dog for you! 

****************************

All PETronus Rescue dogs receive basic vaccinations (distemper/parvo, bordetella, & rabies), spay/ neuter, and microchip prior to adoption. We also treat any know medical issues, including heartworms.

Our dogs live in foster homes while they wait patiently for their forever families to find them. This is beneficial in that they learn house manners, crate training, housebreaking, etc while they wait and we are also able to get a very realistic picture of their energy level, temperament, etc so that we can place them in a home that is the best fit.

Our adoption fees are $200 for dogs over 1 year of age and $250 for dogs under 1 year of age. Puppies receive 3 rounds of puppy vaccinations.

If you are interested in adopting one of our amazing dogs, please fill out our adoption application here http://bit.do/PRAdoption and we will be in touch!

animal.description:
Bella means beautiful and that is exactly what she is. She is gorgeous. She is also crazy (but in the good kind of ways) crazy cute, crazy smart, crazy talented, crazy athletic and crazy amazing.

Don't let her sweet face and shy smile fool you! This girl can jump 0-7 feet in nothing flat, she knows how to scale a chain link fence and her zoomies will make your head spin. She is amazingly athletic and if you are interested in harnessing a dog's physical prowess for sports or performance, she is your girl!

One of her favorite things is a drive-by belly rub, that is, if you are fast enough to reach down for it when she flips over at your feet for one split second. Have we used the word firecracker yet? Deep down Bella has an endless desire for fun and games, but because she is so agile and strong, this has led to her creating the game of I Escape-You Find Me! 

Bella lived with a family in Oklahoma for the first year of her life but escaped from her yard so many times, the family agreed to hand her over to a rescue who contacted Search Dog. She has many of the qualities that we look for, especially her physical abilities, but her fun-loving nature overpowered her focus for work.

Bella really loves to run (and jump and play) so she will need someone that has the ability to offer her the time and space to get her ya ya's out. She would be a terrific athletic partner and a wonderful friend for running, hiking, and playing.

This girl loves everyone and everything, but would love to love you most of all!

Bella is just over one year old and weighs 50 pounds. She is spayed and up to date on her vaccinations.

animal.description:
Nero is a 1yr old, 34lb Whippet/Basenji mix looking for his perfect match. 

Please read to the end.
Nero is a gentle soul and total love with a mildly energetic side. He loves to cuddle and just hang out. Nero will be your bestest friend.  But this requires a very patient person who is willing to put in the time. If this is not you do not even contact us, don't waste our time, this great dog needs a great home with someone who will love him.

Nero loves butt scratches, will push it up against you even for just a little pat. Oh and when rubbing his chest or belly and you hit that perfect spot his leg moves a mile a minute. He likes to spend time on the couch and will snuggle up on your lap. Nero absolutely loves cat lasers and could chase them all day. He does play with toys mostly the ones with squeakers or balls.This guy loves quality soft treats, and knows the sound of the treat bag well. They are a best Friend maker with him for sure.

Nero is house broke, crate trained. He walks good on a leash but is collar sensitive. We are working on this. Nero is great with other dogs as long as they aren't pushy with him. No cats and no young kids. Teens are ok.

Now that said Nero came to us scared to death and exhibiting fear aggression. After his arrival we soon discovered he likely suffered abuse at the hands of humans at some point. Needless to say life for Nero has not been great. It takes time for Nero to trust but once he does, once he opens up he is just marvelous.

Nero needs a calm, child and cat free home with a secure fence. He needs people who will let him come out of his shell on his own. A family who will love him and understand his needs. Nero needs another dog already in the home as this will help him open up and adjust. We consider Nero a project dog. He is the best kind of project as in the end you will find a best friend, a loving companion and the best addition to your family you could ask for.

Adoption fee $300

Nero is neutered, UTD on da2lpp & rabies, de-wormed, heartworm tested, on flea/tick/heartworm prevention and microchipped.

If interested in Nero the first step is to submit an application at pinealoperescue.net/application

animal.description:
Hi there,  my name is Tripp, I only have 3 legs so you know how I got my name. A while back,  I ended up at the animal shelter because my owners could no longer care for me. It was a scary place but now I realize it was the best thing as some really nice rescue people bailed me out. I am a young guy and even though I am missing a leg, I am active and would love to have a nice big fenced yard to run in. I get along well with other dogs but I am sometimes a little bossy so a fur sibling who is not dominant would be best. I am also ok to be an only dog and get all the attention.. I am housebroken and I don't mind spending time in the crate when no humans are home. Cats, they are ok as long as they don't run from me, that makes them fun to chase. I am also content to snuggle on the couch and hope to find a furever home that will let me do that. I don't remember how I lost my leg but it doesn't really matter, I am on to bigger and better things. I really love treats and will do almost anything for them so I am looking forward to getting lots of them and learning new things. I love going for car rides. I really want to be part of a family. I prefer a nice quiet home so one with no young kids would be best. 

A very generous donor has offered to pay for a cart for me to use when going on long walks and for when I am not as young and rambunctious as I am now so my cart will come with me. I can run and jump just like any normal dog and my foster mom treats me just like the dogs who have all their legs.
My foster mom says that everyone who meets me falls in love, you could be next......

All dogs are adopted out up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines. All dogs over 6 months of age are spayed and neutered prior to adoption. Puppies under 6 months of age are adopted out on spay/neuter contracts and must be fixed before 6 months of age.

animal.description:
Meet Tuxedo and Zayla in Taos, New Mexico. They could be transported to Colorado for the right home!!!

Zayla and Tuxedo were found on a property where they were fending for themselves due to an unfortunate situation that had been going on for quite a while. A wonderful group of people made it their mission to save these 2 senior dogs along with several other animals that were left on the property, and they are now at a shelter waiting for a new home and family and happier days. 

Tuxedo is the handsome 11 year old Chow-Shepherd mix with a wonderful personality. He is starving for attention and love, and will nudge at you to keep petting him if you stop. He will even try to get all of his 60 pounds up into your lap if you let him. He has some arthritis and could stand to lose a few pounds, but he couldn’t be any sweeter!

Zayla is 14 years old and we think she is a Lab-Shepherd mix. She is the shyer of the 2, and looks to Tuxedo for reassurance and comfort. Zayla will warmup to people given time, patience and a gentle touch. If you crouch down and talk to her, her little tail will start going and you’ll know you are winning her over. Her arthritis is pretty advanced so we are looking for a home where she doesn’t have to navigate too many stairs. 

This sweet old pair has been through thick and thin together, so we are trying to find them a loving home together where they can be spoiled and live out their retirement as cherished furry family members. We think they would do fine with other respectful dogs. We are partnering with Stray Hearts Animal Shelter - Taos, NM to find Zayla and Tuxedo the retirement home of their dreams. Finding a home for a senior bonded pair can be hard, so please help us spread the word so that we can help make it happen. And if you are interested potentially adopting this amazing duo please fill out our online adoption survey: https://www.olddogsnewdigs.com/adoption-survey/
Thanks!!!

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior pets have a history of being kept up to date on vaccines, annual exams and recommended bloodwork. We also do home checks to make sure that your home environment meets the needs of the particular dog you are interested in.

If you’re interested in adoption, please fill out our online adoption survey at https://www.olddogsnewdigs.com/adoption-survey/
