animal.description:
Hi! I'm Mama Joyce or Mama for short! I am a 6 year old pretty female American Staffy. I came into the shelter as a stray. Before that, I wasn't treated very well and I was used as a breeding dog. Then when I couldn't have anymore puppies, they threw me away like a piece of trash. That hurt my feelings. Now MAR has me in a wonderful foster home where I can be calm and feel safe. Though my foster Dad loves me so much, he would be happy for me if I found my very own home. I might prefer to be the queen of my castle, or I might do okay with a well balanced larger male. Little dogs scare me, and I tend to bark at them. I like treats very much, and I will try just about anything for them when offered as a reward. I am crate trained, but do I wouldn’t mind being a cuddle partner if you were so inclined. I'm house trained and will wait to be taken outside to go potty.  I'm a very sweet girl with medium energy and I LOVE tummy rubs!  I LIVE for tummy rubs! I can't decide what i love more, treats or tummy rubs! I do have a little separation anxiety,  but my foster Dad is working with me on that. My back, left leg bothers me a bit, so I need a soft place to sleep. I would be a very loving, affectionate, happy, goofy, obedient companion for anyone. If you would like to learn more or meet me, contact Martina Animal Rescue at: 
Martinaanimalrescue@yahoo.com

Application, home check and adoption fee required.

animal.description:
****Please do not send us inquiries/emails asking if this puppy is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. See the bottom of this bio for more FAQs regarding our adoption process before emailing.****

Name: Chance

Age: 6 months

Current Weight: 18 lbs

Health: up to date on required vaccinations, neutered, hind-end paralyzed and is urine incontinent due to his injury (wears a belly band indoors). Physical therapy recommended (his foster mom can provide more information about that!)

Chance is a fun loving little spit fire. He loves to play rough and tumble with the big dogs! That’s his absolute favorite thing. He loves every person and dog he meets. He wants to be everyone’s friend. Despite his disability he gets around awesome in or out of his cart. When he’s not wildly playing he is either being  mischievous or resting his head on your lap. He is a curious funny guy who would fit into almost any home.  Chance needs a playmate. A home with a very playful larger dog (he’s small but loves the bigger dogs) would be amazing. Chance is not urine continent. He does wear a belly band which is an easy solution for a dog like Chance. It is possible some day he could walk again. Physical therapy is suggested.   

Adoption fee: $300

To apply to adopt Chance, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING

**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
"Zoey" is an Australian Kelpie who originally went into a shelter in Sheridan, WY as a stray whose age at that time was estimated to be 2-3 years.  She was adopted and for the past year has lived in a very loving home.  She was great with two autistic boys and tries to get the two cats to play.  Due to a divorce situation, this single mom can no longer give "Zoey" the attention or exercise she needs as she has a very small yard and limited time with her family.  

"Zoey" has a severely damaged rear leg that was never repaired when she was young.  It has grown back with the ball of her hip removed from the socket and is now deformed, but most of all she lives with pain which will only get worse with age.  Because she is such a sweet and active girl, we raised $1,500 for her surgery.  She will be at the vet clinic for a week and then 3 weeks in recovery in a foster home.  Because she is young and healthy and a very durable working breed, we feel this expense will totally change her life. You can follow her progress on our Facebook page.

"Zoe" is very nicely house trained, spayed, microchipped and will be brought current on all her vaccinations.  She is good with people of all ages and can be protective of her family.  This breed is exceptionally smart and eager to please.

For an appointment to meet "Zoey," please email kathy@3dogrescue.com for an application that can be filled out online.  Her adoption fee is $200 and she will come with complete vet records, microchip registration and various supplies.  We do not adopt to families with children under the age of 5 and we prefer to find homes within a 200 more radius of the Cody/Powell area.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Brownie (GA) is a 3 year old female Basset Hound blend who comes to rescue from a S. Georgia shelter and a broken home. Her previous owner went to jail and prior to doing so had also killed two other dogs. Upon intake in mid Nov 2020, Brownie weighed 41 pounds and had already been spayed. You can imagine what her life had been previously. Brownie doesnt appear on intake to be well socialized to a leash, but our veterinary partner will work with her a little prior to coming north. She will get scared and refuse to walk. Her perfect home would be one with a fenced yard, quiet, and with a patient family. She needs someone who understands that she may need some space during decompression time just to get used to the idea of being safe and for her to explore her new home. Brownie is a good girl and she really just needs to know nothing but kindness every day for the rest of her life. If you have a compassionate heart, a quiet home, a kind touch and soft words of love to whisper and would like to do so and adopt Brownie, please put your application in here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org

animal.description:
Hi my name is Atticus, and I'm a 9 year old Pitbull Terrier.

- I am a SNUGGLE bud, and the epitome of a couch potato! I am happy just laying around all day and snuggle up with my human. That being said, I also love going on my walks, playing tug with my toys, and going everywhere with you!!

- I am a love bug and great with everyone!! I am a very easy going pup, and I'd love for you to take me everywhere you go!

- I love to play with dogs my size, and hang out with them!

- I have some GI issues which simply means I will need to be on a specific GI food for the rest of my life, but that doesn't affect me more than the type of food my adopter will need to buy. 

- I had an overall unfortunate life, with a lot of abandonment and abuse throughout, but I still have a lot of trust in humans and can't wait to find my forever snuggle family!!

- In April, I was rescued by the HIT LIVING team the afternoon I was supposed to be euthanized. Shortly after I was rescued, I was adopted by my foster! Sadly, and to no fault of my own, I was returned to the foundation 6 months later, after I wasn’t being set up for success with my adopter. I am now ready to go to my actual forever home, who will truly care and love me forever!

- I will be very happy with any sort of situations, apt or house, men or women! I will be better in a home without small children who could scare me, cats or small dogs. 

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
Hi I'm Nana! I'm a 1 year old, 55lb Belgian Shepherd/Malinois. I am young and energetic, and will need an adopter who can truly provide the right amount of exercise and adventures in my life! 

- I unfortunately came from an abusive and traumatic past, so I am still quite shy at first and I can get frightened easily.

- Despite my past I am an energetic, loving, cuddly and loyal girl! I am VERY active and will need an adopter who can provide the correct amount of outdoor activity for me throughout the day.

- I love other dogs, am learning to coexist with cats, AND even chilling with the pigs who live in my current foster home. I will actually need to be adopted out to a family who has another playful doggo, so I can learn from them and play all day!

- I still need some time to start trusting men again as I am still very fearful of them. However, I have been working on that with my foster family by receiving meals, going on walks, and even getting gentle cuddles from my foster dad.

- Once I feel safe, I am an absolute joy and a total goofball!

My ideal home would have:
- Another dog to learn from, play with, and build up my confidence
- A yard to run around in
- A very active owner with time dedicated to me
- No young children who could possibly frighten me

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
If submitting an adoption application for Misty you must note on your application that you ahve read her entire posting and understand her needs.

Misty is almost 14 yrs old and is right around 13 lbs. Adopted out from a CA shelter in 2016 she was picked up as a stray in October and ended up back in the shelter in an unbelievable state. Her hair was so matted it was cutting into the skin on her legs and choking her. She had an oozing cyst on her neck, and her eyes, ears, and teeth all infected. The matting was so bad it partially detached her right back paw (strangulation by mats), and caused a deep wound on her right front leg.

This little lady can't see or hear any more, but her heart and will are strong. In spite of having one of her back paws almost completely severed off by matt strangulations she still manages, and is quite determined, to hobble around limited areas on her own. Full senior blood work and kidney functions tested good. She's also had a dental.

Misty's match is going to be an adopter looking for a goldfish companion in a dog's body. She not one for being held or coddled, in fact if you try to hold her she'll do her best to wiggle out of your hold. She's cute to keep watch over in her little penned in areas though. A grown man's snore coming out of her little body is also quite amusing. Her eyes and ears may have failed her, but her nose is good. She really enjoys sniffing excursions in the yard and seems to enjoy being taken out for walks in a dog stroller or the dog pouch her foster uses for on walks.

Misty needs an adopter who is willing to watch over and care for her without expecting her to be a warm cuddly companion in return. If you can find a soft spot in your heart for a strong willed quirky little Goldfish dog, we'd love to see this girl placed with an adopter who will give her the space and care she more than deserves in her sunset years.

Because of her limited sight and visions she has to have set x-pen space in the home (her own little oversized goldfish bowl) to be and feel safe. She is good being taken outside to potty, but also makes use of pee pads in her penned in area. She requires regular grooming, which is no easy task. She is a lot stronger and more wiggly than seems possible for a dog her age when she gets scared and grooming is scary to her. She's had to be sedated by a vet for her last couple of grooms and will likely need to continue to be sedated for groomings going forward.

All Underdogs are in foster homes. You must have an adoption application on file to request a meet. An online adoption application can be accessed online at https://underdogsrock.org/adopt-a-dog

Misty is part of a special Underdog Elder adoption program. Her adoption fee is $75. A starter bag of food, collar and leash are provided with her adoption. She is spayed, up to date on vaccinations, and microchipped.

For updates on all the Underdogs be sure to follow us Underdogs Rock Rescue on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/UnderdogsRockRescue

COVID PRECAUTIONS:

Meets are part of the Underdog adoption process and will take place outside, masks required. Home checks are also part of the process and will be conducted virtually. Additionally all paperwork, including adoption contract signatures, will be through email.

Toga is nine-months old as of late Jan '21, great with other dogs to include small dogs. Her owner felt they did not have the room for her. She is an active gal, loves attention, loves to play, great for an active family, about 45 lbs right now.

ADOPTION FEES Dogs & Puppies.....$100.00 . This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more.
The first step to do an adoption is to do our Adoption Application here: https://www.elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
Yes, there are sometimes exceptions to our normal fee for older dogs or special cases. Some of our pets have also been lovingly sponsored by caring people and we will let the approved adopter know about that at the point of adoption. Visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org The staff would also like to remind you that for faster response to inquiries about adoptable animals to have the animals ID#, name & description. This way your questions will be answered in a timely manner.
All pet adoption websites & our shelter management software require that we choose a primary and/or secondary breed for our dogs. While our staff is quite breed knowledgeable, in many cases we are truly making our best guesses as to their breed(s) based on many factors but cannot promise that what we have said is accurate. So taking into account your own parameters for things such as size, coat care, activity level, etc please come and get to know our dog(s) as individuals to see if their personalities and yours are a forever match.
Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Nadia and I’m a 2-year-old, female mini German Shepard mix.

**I have fear bite history in my past and have been working and living with my trainer, Aubrey of Beezy's Pack. She has created structure for me which I never had before as I was pregnant and living on the streets of Mexico. She has allowed me to be the pup that I never got to be so that I feel confident. I need someone who can continue my training and has the potential financial recourses and time to commit to keeping me active with structure and routine. I need a yard and will need to be in a home with no children, small pets or other dogs at this time**

- It takes me a short while to warm up to new people but once I do I am so full of life, a cuddle bug and a total joy to be around!

- I just had 7 babies and was the best mama to them but now I'm looking to love and be loved by a new family!

- I want all the belly rubs I can get. Once I'm warmed up to you I will happily and consistently show you my belly for some good belly rubs.

- Walkies please! I have a good amount of energy so I need a few walks a day, one of which is preferably a bit longer than just around the block so I can get my energy out! 

- I still have a bit of over-protective mother tendencies so I am working on not getting overly protective of things like toys and my humans, which is why I would prefer a home without another dog to share my things with. Although I am being fostered with several other dogs, I do like all the attention to be on me and prefer to be an only child at home :)

My perfect home would have:
- No other pets or young children who could scare me with their brusk movements
- A devoted and experienced dog-loving individual or family
- A backyard or outdoor area to run around

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Online Adoption Application 
Hi I'm Anna! I'm back - unfortunately I was returned to the rescue. So I'm on my search again for my true furever family. I originally came to the rescue just a day away from a bad fate - I'd ended up at a rural county shelter...no longer wanted by my previous owner...a bully breed, pregnant and an owner surrender - that is not a recipe for success in getting out of a shelter. But, Pawfect Match heard about me and had a foster home available for a knocked up girl like myself and the rest is history. I gave birth to 9 gorgeous puppies (they get it from me) and I was a great mom. All of my puppies have been adopted except Roseland - she was adopted and returned - what a run of bad luck for us both. I'm a gorgeous girl but I am energetic and need training and consistency. I have poor leash manners - I get reactive when I see another dog so I need training and a strong handler who can manage me. A fenced yard would be great - of course dogs need to burn off energy going on walks but while getting my training situated, a fenced yard would be great for me to run and play. Don't get me wrong...I do like to snuggle too. I'm a great medium sized gal. I like some dogs so we'll have to see how things go if you have a resident dog. With patience, true commitment to me, and a consistent schedule, I'm going to be a great addiiton to a family. Is it yours?

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.MARIO IS CURRRENTLY BEING FOSTERED IN ILLINOIS

TODAY WE WELCOME MARIO INTO MASTINO RESCUE. Our new intake is such a stunning tawny boy who turns 2 years old on 11/25 will be having entropion surgery and a full work up with Dr. Joel on Monday. He has lumps on top of hygromas on his knees, is missing hair along with dried out skin and his paws are sore. Being 20 pounds overweight x-rays show loose hips but are uncertain as to what point until a full exam with updated x-rays are completed.

Mario will be fostered in Illinois until his perfect home is found and he has time to recuperate from his eye surgery. This entropion is one of the worst we have seen, clearly the picture shows he is unable to open his eyes which is extremely painful. Just a couple more days and his healing process begins. We are praying that he does not have any permanent sight issues from the eyelashes scratching on his corneas, we are however expecting to see ulcers which will heal with medicated drops.

Although, he is neutered he will be needing much attention, obviously bi-lateral entropion surgery in both eyes, vaccines, fecal, heartworm testing, skin scraping, x-rays and whatever else is needed to get him healthy. At this time we can say he has been sweet during transport but it is unfair at this point to evaluate him due to his physical state.

The perfect home for Mario would be a nice quiet home in the country. His people must be breed specific and willing to help him with his diet, take him on short walks and be patient with decompression time. No children in the home under the age of 18, must own your home, have a 6 foot privacy fence, be the only pet at this time and be able to give him all the love he is deserving of. If you fit the criteria please go to our website at www.mastinorescue.org and complete a Family Profile and a volunteer from our adoption team will contact you.

UPDATE: Mario is recuperating nicely from his entropion surgery and has been started on his diet. He has received several medicated baths and his skin is looking/feeling better already. We see a huge difference in not only his physical appearance but he is much happier. He is now up to date on vaccines, worm and heartworm negative. Could you be his forever home?

More pictures and updates coming. We have you boy so no more worries, your loving home awaits you.

animal.description:
"A diamond in the rough." Hazel is a beautiful playful Great Pyrenees who has exceptional potential. She loves to be around people and can be very affectionate once she gets to know you. Hazel loves to give kisses and enjoys being petted. She will follow you as she likes to stay near her family.

Hazel, born December 2018, weighing about 107 lbs, was an owner surrender to the Great Pyrenees Rescue Society after she started chasing the family's farm animals. She was left outdoors to live and sleep in an open shelter. Her family brought her indoors whenever she got anxious hearing fireworks, and she would stay very close to them for comfort. Her family loved her.

Hazel needs more experience living indoors. Hazel is learning to walk nicely on a leash. She likes people after she gets to know them and likes other dogs although she is very picky who she plays with.

She would do best in a home as an "only dog" with an all adult family, kids 15 years old and older are ok and a cat free home. A large secure fenced yard for play and a daily walk would be a good start for expanding her socialization skills. She will need a family with confident leaders that are familiar with Pyr's traits and behaviors. Are you the family Hazel needs to help her become the best-devoted family companion? If you are, please complete an adoption application for Hazel.

Adoption Fee $325 (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($225). Adoption applications can be found on our website at https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

animal.description:
Marshall is a young fellow who didn't get off to the best start in life. He was kept outdoors and from there it went downhill. He contracted heartworm disease and his owner fell ill and could no longer care for him. Marshall loved the other pet at his original home... a yorkipoo whom Marshall protected and adored. Once Marshall was turned into the shelter, his fortunes started to take a turn for the better. He is now in a loving foster home, sleeping inside and having his heartworm treated.

Marshall has shown curiosity regarding the family cat, but has made no effort to chase or harass her. At less than 2 years old, he's just a goofy, playful, toy loving, chewing puppy. (There's nothing like a chewing puppy to encourage you to pick up your shoes and put them away.) When excited, he will "mouth," which could be mistaken for biting by someone not familiar with puppy behavior, but his fosters are working on curbing that. Because of his size and energy level, we would prefer to place him with older children. Those under the age of 7 or 8 may be bowled over by his non-aggressive exuberance. Marshall would think he hit the lottery if his forever home came with another playful dog, preferably a young one who would love to wrestle and play chase.

Marshall sleeps like a log at night. He currently sleeps in a crate to protect both himself and property while everyone sleeps. He willingly goes into the crate at about 10:00 p.m. if a treat awaits him inside, and he sleeps until about 7:00. He cat naps anywhere he wants during the day, but if his foster mom leaves the room, he wakes and follows her. He finds her daily activities fascinating. Marshall is still learning the art of indoor living, but we think he's done fantastically well in learning household manners. He's had a few minor accidents inside (The one where it was pouring outside doesn't count.), but he's since learned to paw at the back door when he needs to go outside. Because of his curiosity, energy, and general newness at indoor living, Marshall should be crated when left alone.

If you would like to welcome this joyful sweetheart into your home, please complete an Adopter Profile and e-mail it to icanhelp@beaglemaryland.org. .

Marshall's Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vIndividualCurrentDog.aspx?dogid=69882
Adoptable Dog Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vCurrentDogs.aspx

If you'd like to adopt one of our beagles:
*Go to our Website - href="http://beaglemaryland.org
*Review our  Standards for Adoption - http://beaglemaryland.org/Home.aspx?pg=standardsforadoption.htm
*Fill out an Adopter Profile - 
http://brsmbeagles.org/new_site/documents/BRSM_profile_secure.pdf
 and email it to us (or print it off, fill it in and send it via regular mail, if you prefer)
*A BRSM volunteer will contact you to guide you through the rest of the process!

We hope to hear from you, and so do the beagles!

animal.description:
Meet Buster, possibly part Norwich Terrier. He weighs around 12# and is 2 years old. Buster has been with PPAWS since September 2020.
When he came he was very fearful. We have had him evaluated by a trainer who tells us he has several feral traits. The major trait that you would have to accept is that he is very shy to most people. He sometimes barks and growls at new people so to get you to go away. Making new friends is very difficult for him. It would be several weeks before he could show that he trusts you and wag his happy tail. He would hide in his kennel if you kept an eye on him. While not being watched, he will explore.
What Buster needs is a daily structure. Doing the same thing day after day. Over the last few months we have discovered that he loves to go for a walk. His leash manners are superb. He struts himself like he owns the world.
To help with his fearfulness Busters forever home would be best to have a partner dog, to help guide him how a dog fits into your home, he would love a fenced yard to do his exploring and squirrel chasing. His wire crate is his safe place when he is scared, and because he can be ornery, it is best to kennel him when you need to be gone. He will go to his kennel upon command. Small or young children can be somewhat unpredictable, so probably best he not live with small children.
As you can see, this boy is special and will take a very special home. He is not a lap dog at this time, but if you get down to his level he loves belly rubs and scratches, it makes him smile. If you think you are interested in finding out more about Buster. Please fill out an application.
https://www.purple-paws.

animal.description:
Regardless of her rough start to life, Lucha has never once given up hope. She has more than lived up to her full name; Luchadora which translates to fighter. She is a precious 5-month-old terrier mix who weighs around 30 pounds. This tough girl now rocks a cute wheelchair to get around easier yet she is still faster than the speed of lightning. Diapers nor wheelchairs can bring Lucha down! She is unstoppable and a true inspiration to all. With a heart of gold, she gets along great with other dogs, cats, and older children. She loves spending her days chasing lizards, greeting the neighbors on walks, and playing with her favorite toys. She is an expert cuddler and prefers a warm lap over anything. Life improves drastically with Lucha in it and we just know that there is a special family out there for this one of a kind girl! 

Special Needs: Lucha was found abandoned next to a dumpster with severe injuries and in dire need of medical attention. Thanks to the quick thinking and kind hearts of the local firemen who found her, her life was saved from certain death. After further diagnostics, X-rays concluded that Lucha has a congenital defect that was likely present at birth. Some of the vertebrae are pushed together very tightly resulting in partial paralysis. Lucha still has some movement of her tail but does not have full control over her urine or stools.

Lucha is seeking a family that is home most of the day as she does require more attention than a typical dog. She will gladly reward her family with plenty of kisses in return! If you live in the central Florida area, own your home, and think Lucha may be the right pup for you, please fill out a screening form found here: https://mettarescuefamily.org/adoptable-dogs

animal.description: This is our sweet Romeo. His previous owners brought him to the shelter to be euthanized because he was paralyzed due to an unknown trauma. But luckily, the doctors saw potential in him and suggested to have him surrendered instead. One of the wonderful doctors took Romeo home to foster, and after a few weeks of physical therapy, Romeo began walking again! When he was cleared to be pulled by a rescue, we welcomed this handsome boy into the AMA family. He still sways a bit when he lifts his leg for peeing and may fall here and there from jumping attempts, but overall he's steady on his feet. He is housebroken and good with other pets. Romeo is great with people and super affectionate. If you'd like to have Romeo join your family, please fill out the adoption application at https://amaanimalrescue.org/pet/romeo/

animal.description:
“Pearls were accidents, and the finding of one was luck, a little pat on the back by God or the gods or both.” - John Steinbeck, The Pearl

Welcome Pearl! This precious girl is 11-months old and about 30 pounds at the moment, but we think she may gain another 10 or so before she’s fully grown! 

Pearl is pretty new to housebreaking and crate-training, but is she getting better every day. She is able to sleep all night long, and she doesn’t need to be let out for a midnight bathroom break. She knows that she is supposed to go outside to potty, but she’s still learning how to tell her foster mom when it’s time. Pearl is getting used to her crate, but she won’t go in on command yet. She doesn’t love that she’s been sequestered from everyone else in the house, but after a few minutes she’s able to settle down and relax.

Pearl LOVES spending time with other dogs, and she particularly loves to cuddle with her big brother Mango; she would love to be in a home with some dog friends. Based on what we can tell so far in the time we’ve had Pearl, she seems like the kind of girl everyone loves to be around!

When Pearl meets a new face, she can be on the bashful side, but if the person has a treat, she is very quick to overcome that shyness and will be their new best friend. Pearl prefers to be around people, but she can be slow to give affection. If she’s giving away a kiss or lays her head down on your lap, you know you’ve made it! 

Pearl is getting more adjusted to the world every day! Foster mom says she’s even started venturing into the fenced yard to run, jump, and play. Like a lot of puppies her age, Pearl definitely benefits from getting outside and getting some of those puppy wiggles out. Running around outside, chasing a ball, or daily walks would be great exercise for her, and once she gains some more confidence, she might like a trip to go play with some friends at the dog park. Once she’s had her exercise for the day, this girl loves to settle in on the couch for some cuddles and a nap.

This pearl of a girl may not have had the best beginnings in life, but she is sure to shine in the right setting. Could it be with you? Contact us today! 

If you’d like to be considered to adopt, the first step in the process is to submit an application through our website: http://athenscaninerescue.com/adoption-procedures/. Our adoption fee is $250 per dog over the age of 6 months and $300 per dog 6 months or younger. We accept payment by Venmo, PayPal, or card.

This includes: basic vet care (i.e. basic vaccinations, including boosters completed after adoption, spay/neuter, heartworm/flea preventatives, and treatment for any health needs while in our care), a microchip, a week’s worth of food for the trial-period, and a harness lead.

We typically adopt to homes within 30 minutes of Athens, GA, as we require a basic home check to ensure all dogs are placed in a safe environment. If you are further away than that and are interested in one of our pups, please still fill out an application and we can discuss your options. WE ARE CURRENTLY NOT ACCEPTING OUT OF STATE APPLICATIONS. 

We do not have a facility and operate through a network of foster homes. Thus, we do not have a phone number. If you’d like to discuss potential adoptions, please email at adopt@athenscaninerescue.com.

animal.description:
Meet Dillon! He's about a year and a half old and about 50 pounds. Dillon came to us as an owner surrender so we have some background information provided to us by his previous owners. 

Dillon is very smart and quick to pick up things. According to his previous owners he is house trained and crate trained. His owners even said that they were able to teach him to use a specific part of the yard to go potty in within a couple of days! Dillon is fine spending time in his crate and will sleep through the night fine in it.

Dillon is still learning what toys he likes best. He needs someone patient enough to train him how to walk well on a leash. Dillon is also dog aggressive so long walks in very ""dog popular"" neighborhoods won't be ideal for Dillon. He is just fine kicking back in his backyard when he needs to go potty to avoid the stress of seeing other dogs. Dillon has been voted by staff as Best Belly-Rub Receiver and cutest trotter.

If your home is in need of exactly one dog, Dillon is an ideal guy for you! He is so well mannered and friendly to humans. He hasn't been tested around cats but has been known to chase birds and squirrels so his ideal home wouldn't have any cats.

Dillon is up to date on his shots and monthly flea/tick, neutered, microchipped, and heart worm negative!

animal.description:
Drake is a happy boy who loves interacting at the fence lines with the other dogs in the runs next to him and seeing who he can beat to the other end. He's also an avid squirrel stalker and keeps frogs to a minimum in our big dog runs; pesky things frogs....they keep jumping away from you or up into your face!

Drake was adopted from us in 2016 and lived in that home until 2020 when his mom got sick and could no longer care for him. He was morbidly obese, very timid and shy and sad for a long time after coming back. But he's been on weight management dog food, has lots of exercise and he's like a new dog! Drake doesn't mind other dogs but enjoys being the single focus in a home, like he was used to. He'd probably do fine with another dog whose energy level is equal to his and would not demand too much engagement from him. Drake has a lot of good years left; he just needs the right family to spend it with.

animal.description:
Hello! My name is Turbo and I just had a photoshoot. Don't I look so glamorous? My new photos truly show off my personality. Here's a bit about me:

I am a 1.5 year old and 45lb. I am up to date on shots and neutered so I'm ready to go!

My favorite thing to do is run around in the yard. My foster mom says I have a lot of energy and like to stay active. Sometimes she says I can be a lot and need a moment to calm down. I love to learn and foster mom has been teaching me Sit, Down, Stay, Wait, Go to Bed, Outside, and Leave It. I also learned how to use a little bell to go outside. Foster mom says it helps her know when I need a potty break.

I'm still getting used to leash walking but I like to explore. Exploring is the bestest! Chasing small critters (SQUIRREL!) is super fun too but foster mom has been working on teaching me that not all animals need to be chased when I'm walking with her.

One of my favorite places is my crate. I make myself at home in there and sleep there at night. Sometimes, you may even hear me snoring. I promise it's cute!

Did I mention I LOVE to snuggle. Foster mom says I'm a "love bug" and I give lots of hugs and kisses. I absolutely love to show my hoomans I think they're great.

I'd love to have a playmate at my new home. One of my favorite things to do is play chase. I can do that FOREVER... and ever... and ever! I also like to wrestle but foster mom says I'm still learning how to not play too hard. She says it's important for me to have a dog playmate that can keep up with me and even teach me new things. She also says I'd be okay as an only dog but I'd need an outlet for all my energy. Maybe we could try agility or fly ball!!!??? It would be great to end each day tired.

Because I love to jump and run, I may knock over little kiddos. Foster mom says I should watch where I'm going but I cannot help it! I have energy. I'm going to be better off in a home with teens or adults.

Ready to adopt me? I promise to look super cute in bandanas and be your best friend!

BCRRT is a Texas based rescue with fosters in TX and OK. Our adoption areas are TX, OK and surrounding states. We do not allow shipping/transport of dogs to other states. If you are interested and would like to apply please visit: https://bcrrt.com/adoption/ and fill out an application form.

animal.description:
Bonnie!

If you are looking for a sweet & snuggly little lady that rarely stops wagging her tail, look no further! Beautiful Bonnie is currently being spoiled & loved in Foster Care, but is now ready for her forever family to see her & fall in love! She has really come out of her shell since leaving the Shelter, learning to trust & showing off her bubbly but gentle personality! Getting her into her forever home as soon as possible would be ideal for this loving little lady so she can start to settle in!

Bonnie originally came into Maricopa County Animal Care & Control's West Shelter emotionally shut down & carrying a massive mammary tumor (approximately 1/4 of her total weight). After only being at the Shelter a short time, Bonnie needed to leave immediately for much needed veterinary care the Shelter was not going to provide. 2nd Chance Dog Rescue stepped in quickly to save her precious life! Bonnie had her extremely large tumor removed & has healed wonderfully! While her mass was confirmed to be malignant, clean margins were obtained, & further diagnostics could not find any evidence it had spread! Bonnie has had full blood work, x-rays, is up-to-date on shots, & has her next appointment already set up to be spayed & have a doggie dental!

Bonnie is approximately 8 years old & although only a DNA test could confirm, everyone's best guess is that she is the combination of a Chihuahua & Beagle! She is a petite 12lbs, walks well on a leash, & is housebroken. She is timid with strangers, but once she knows you are a friend she attaches quickly & craves human attention! Belly rubs are her most favorite 'activity' & her non-stop tail wags will have you smiling all day long! Did I mention those EYES!? Her beautiful brown Beagle eyes will melt your heart!

She enjoys attention from her Foster siblings (of all sizes), & often seeks them out to spend time with & to snuggle with of course! She is a bit shy with play so far & toys are a bit scary, but she keeps everyone entertained with her zoomies & play bows! Of course, introductions with current doggie family members are required! Due to her timid demeanor, she would not likely do well with kids, and it takes her a little time to warm up to new people, especially men.

To learn more about this SWEET soul please fill out an application for Bonnie!
https://2ndchance.rescuegroups.org/animals/detail?AnimalID=16270573

animal.description:
We’d like to introduce you to Miley! Miley is a young Mastiff/Labrador mix who is only about 1 year old. Miley came to Green Hills Animal Shelter as a rescue, and even though she has only been at the shelter since November 14th, she has already stolen the hearts of the staff, volunteers and everyone who has met her.

Miley, who sports a beautiful black and cream brindled coat, came to the shelter as a rescue. Sadly, she came from a situation where she was not treated very kindly, and it appears that at some point she may have even been shot with a pellet gun.  Despite her tough past, however, Miley is the sweetest girl you could ever hope to meet, and is full of love, joy and lots of happiness to share.

Miley is a very energetic dog who loves to play and who keeps us laughing with her silliness and goof-ball antics. If you were to ask her what her favorite 3 things in the world are, we have no doubt that Miley would answer, “attention, kids and cats!”

If Miley could describe her perfect forever home, she would ask for an active home where she could receive lots of attention and be a loved and treasured member of her family.  She would love to be able to romp and play in a securely fenced yard and to go on long, leashed walks. She would enjoy a home with children and perhaps a kitty friend or two, but she would prefer to be the only dog in the household.

Miley will go to her Forever Home spayed, de-wormed, heartworm tested, and up to date on all her vaccinations, including rabies.  This sweet girl had a rough start, but she is more than ready to put it all behind her and share her joy for life with a family of her very own; could that family be yours?

For more information on Miley or any of the other pets waiting for their Forever Homes at Green Hills Animal Shelter, please phone the shelter at 660-359-2700 or stop by during our normal business hours.  We’ll be honored to introduce you and perhaps help you find a new four-legged friend.

Meet Sally and Charlie.!!! These bonded Great Pyrenees/ mixes are about 5 and one half months old.

These two are some what timid while on leash but off leash they are much bolder.. 
They are friendly duo. ...they are also crazy and 100% untrained. But in their favor they like cats and other dogs..and PEOPLE!
So we begun the slow process of training them while we search for an adoptive family to continue that training. For the last few nights they have had no accidents in their kennel. Sally will sit on command for about 2 seconds before she launches herself at you in unbridled excitement . Charlie....will think about sitting. He starts to sit. ... but will have second thoughts and launch with his sister.
We may be crazy ourselves trying to place these two as a pair. They do seem bonded so we will try.
A securely fenced yard is required

animal.description:
Chavo is a handsome Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler.  Before rescue, he was often seen foraging in the local dump and traveling busy roads. He ended up hit by a car, and was facing death. Mayberry 4 Paws stepped in and got him the medical care and surgery he needed to continue living his life. 

From there, he went to the most amazing foster home where he is loved dearly.  But now, Chavo needs a forever home. He looking for a warm place with land to explore with his family.  He loves being at the creek, walking through the fields, and lounging on the porch, while you enjoy your coffee. . He's a bit bossy and set in his ways,  but so was your ex and that didn't stop you. 

He's an old guy,  but doesn't let his 17 years slow him down much. He loves walks in the great outdoors,  his toys, and his person.  He isn't much on kids or competition.  He prefers to it to be just him and his peeps, taking on the world. Therefore, Chavo would be happiest in a home with adults only. 

Due to his injuries, he does walk a little wonky and appears a little "broken" but he is perfectly imperfect and is in amazing health for his age.  

Does Chavo sound like the dude for you? He won't screw you over your ex did. So,  you can't go wrong. If you're interested, jump on over to our website (www.mayberry4paws.com), click on the FORMS tab and grab an adoption application.  Submit your completed app to mayberry4paws@gmail.com.

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Although Chavo lives with other dogs currently, he would be best suited for a single pet home or a home where he is "boss dog".

Estrella (Star) is a Poodle Mix, rescued from the streets in the Dominican Republic. She is initially very shy as she has experienced abandonment, abuse, and neglect. It takes some time for her to warm up to new situations but once she knows you are her friend she is very sweet, loyal, and engaging. She is current on shots, spayed, and microchipped. Estrella will require a household where there are no children, and adopters understand that her adoption is a labor of patience and above all love. This little girl is a jewel in the rough, one that you can awake and will become your most devoted companion. Estrella appears to be afraid of male figures. She barks at men from a distance. This behavior is being addressed. 

Viewers interested in adopting Estrella should complete the pre-adoption application available in this post. https://form.123formbuilder.com/5081187// A fenced-in-yard and a home visit are requirements for her adoption. Given the current pandemic, home visits are completed following CDC recommendations. Use of face masks and gloves as well as interaction in open spaces, i.e. your backyard. For residents residing beyond or travel time (1.5 hours from our location) or residents out of state, we complete the home visit "virtually" using Google Duo a free application available for all smartphones. This allows for a face-to-face interview, as well as viewing your yard and you getting to see the dog of your choice in "person". We advise interested residents to call us if there are further questions, 850.270.8793 7 am-7 pm

animal.description:
Tank
Pit Bull Mix
Male
5 years old
63 lbs.

Hey there friends, my name is Tank, and I’m a gentle, independent, sweet guy who will be your very best friend for life if you decide to be my forever family!

I’m at my happiest when I’m curled up near my person, whether it’s on the couch or on a big pile of pillows and blankets. That said, I do like talking short walks and I do get the zoomies and sprint around the back yard. I’ve also got a great tail wag that moves my whole butt back and forth when I get excited.

I’m a really friendly pup and I enjoy meeting new people and saying hi to everyone when I’m out on walks! I am friendly to other dogs overall when seeing them out of the house but I seem to prefer the ladies more than other male dogs. But I think I’d just prefer being the only dog in the house overall as I’ve had a few issues with sharing my space/resource guarding when dogs visit my foster home.  I haven’t met any cats so I can’t confirm how I’d do with cat friends and I think I’d do best in a home without young kids just since I haven’t had any experience with kiddos yet in my life. 

One thing to note is that I likely have small tears in my cruciate ligaments. The vet doesn’t recommend surgery at this time since it is a partial tear and they can possibly heal with some inflammatory medication and time. However, I’m looking for a family who would be 1000% ready to take on the cost and recovery support of surgery down the road if my ligaments don’t heal or do completely tear at the recommendation of a vet (cost of a future surgery would be about $1,000 and then I’d be all healthy from there!) and again, there’s a good chance I won’t need it! 

Are you looking for a new BFF? Email my friends at adopt@pawscoadoptions.org and check out this information page: https://pawsco.org/adopt/adoption-process.

animal.description:
This is Mama Tilly Marie who was rescued after being abandoned by her family after she had 11 puppies. Luckily, a Good Samaritan found her, and AAU stepped in to keep her and her babies safe. I was lucky enough to foster Tilly Marie and her babies starting in mid-November. So, we've had some time to get to know her.

It's clear that Tilly Marie had a rough start to life even before she bore, nursed, and took care of her 11 puppies. She is afraid of everything outside of her day-to-day routine. She does not yet walk confidently on a leash although we are working on it. She is afraid of new people, places, sounds, etc. She is in no way aggressive. Her fear manifests itself as just shrinking back into herself and hiding.

She is as sweet as can be in our home and backyard. All she wants is a solid routine and love love love. If we are sitting, she wants to sit with us. If we are taking a walk through the backyard, then she will walk with us. If I'm sleeping, she wants to be next to me. She adores my children, but was very hesitant with my husband for weeks. Eventually, she has warmed up to him and even sleeps right next to him now. Well, sort of in between the two of us.

The honest truth is that I don't know when or if Tilly Marie will be a 'normal' dog who goes on walks and lives without fear. She will need a family that is patient with her as she continues on her journey. She really doesn't demand much, is completely non-destructive when we leave the house, and is just a quiet, calm friend to have around. She really would do well in a home with a steady routine where she can be with her owners as much as possible.

If you are still reading this, then I haven't scared you yet. So, let's get to the Heartworms. Oh, did I forget to mention that this poor thing is also heartworm positive?

Tilly Marie will need heartworm shots to recover. She is eligible to start injections the week of February 8th, but can wait to start til 3/5 at the latest. Until then, s
he can be somewhat normal with playing and walks. She currently gets some exercise by wrestling with her sister and sometimes taking one little run around the backyard.

Once injections begin, she will have r

estricted activity - short leash walks only - out to potty and back inside to rest. No playing, jumping, running, up & down flights of stairs, etc. NO stress or excitement and definitely no boarding or change of environment. The r

estricted activity will last 60 days minimum, preferably 75 days. A

t least 30 days and no more 45 days later she will get 2nd & 3rd injections (back to back 24 hrs apart) continued restricted activity another 30-45 days.

AAU works with adopters taking a dog through heartworm treatment to find a vet nearest to them. In order for AAU to cover costs it must be done at an AAU vet.

I realize that this is all a lot to ask of a new adopter, but I promise you Tilly Marie is worth it. She just needs the right home with a loving, caring, patient family. She is going to make someone a wonderful, life-long friend. Please no cats.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online. http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

animal.description:
In honor of Cassie KramerI'm thrilled to sponsor the 'Cassie Kramer Transport'! This life-saving transport of these beautiful fur babies is dedicated to my sweet little Cassie Bear. We adopted Cassie (Meridith Hess) from Joyful Rescues in January 2019 after losing our sweet fur daughter Mandy at the age of 13 1/2. We were broken and Cassie has been healing our broken hearts. We love her so much and are so grateful to Joyful Rescues and the Hoss Transport for saving her life! Cassie wants to save more pups like she was saved from a high kill shelter in VA. The names of some of the pups are named after Cassie, our course, Mandy, and Frosty Bear (another of my beloved pups who have passed). Al was my Dad's who was always bringing stray dogs home when I was a little. He loved dogs and so began my love for them. Welcome the 'Cassie Kramer Transport'! JR Volunteer since 2012 - Cheryl Kramer

Bear and his siblings were born around July 12, 2020, and may top out in the 60-65 pound-range when done growing. These pups are happy, healthy, social babies that are ready to move in and liven up your lives! Have you ever snuggled with a hound puppy and their floppy ears? It is absolute heaven! The pup's mother, our Marlene, was also surrendered with the babies and she is a kind hearted, old soul, type of dog that is doing amazing in her new home. If you are interested in one of these adorable, sweet, kids keep in mind they are indeed hounds and you may want to do some reading about them if you are unfamiliar with the breed otherwise get your application in quick! Bear is an adorable red and white pup and we want to be sure you know that his tail had been broken at some point and has a pretty good kink in it making him unique! We have found that Bear adores most veggies and particularly delicata squash.
The Adoption Fee for this dog is $500.00

Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a 'complete' pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY.

Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility. YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES

We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.

Can't Adopt Me? SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link 'Special Instructions to Seller' if you want to note a particular pet
Before you seek to adopt a pet from Joyful Rescues, please read our Pet Adoption page http://www.joyfulrescues.org/pet_adoption.html.

Online Application

animal.description:
Meet Maribel! 

Our blue eyed beauty has been searching for her forever home for almost 7 months and we can’t believe she hasn’t been swooped up yet! Maribel is a 2 year old pit/boxer mix who weighs approximately 55 lbs. She is spayed, up to date on vaccines, and fully vetted. Maribel is also crate and house trained! 

Maribel is a volunteer favorite in our rescue because of her sweet and fun spirit! Maribel is an AMAZING dog and we have no doubt she will make a wonderful addition to your family. Maribel loves all people, including kids, and is just truly a lover at heart. Maribel is the perfect mix of energetic and lazy. She loves her couch snuggles but is also excited to go for an outdoor adventure with you. Honestly if her person is with her Maribel is as happy as can be! Maribel is a true nurturer who loves to take care of her people. If you’re sick Maribel is right by your side providing you comfort and love. If you’ve had a bad day Maribel is there to put a smile on your face and give you kisses. She truly is the perfect girl! 

Maribel does well with other dogs but will need slow introductions to any other pets. She loves her furry foster sister and LOVES LOVES LOVES to play with her! We are happy to talk further about how she would integrate into your home and provide potential adopters with any resources and help we can! 

If you’re interested in adopting Maribel fill out our adoption application at the link below 
www.bullluvablepaws.org/adopt

animal.description:
Sherie, confident and loyal lady. 
Hi there! My name is Sherie I am a 4 year old, 50 lbs beautiful lady. I am very loving and human oriented! 
I am crate trained and housetrained, I am good with other dogs but at first encounters I let them know I want to call the shots. I am very loyal and once I bond with a human you are my best friend for ever and I will follow all your instructions and lead.  I am one of those dogs that look for instruction and leadership from my pet parent. How did I ended in rescue? My foster mom drives the same route to work every day, she used to see my friend Otto in the pics with me and me outside a mechanic shop. We were neglected and dirty. She asked him if he needed help with us and he surrendered us immediately! My foster mom wasn’t even ready to take us but she was so afraid he would change his mind she immediately put is in her car and drove away!
Otto and I are still best buddies but my foster mom thinks we will do well going to separate forever homes. Otto is very submissive to me and lets me get away with anything. 
We love inquiries and questions through Petfinder but we receive so many is impossible for us to answer, the best way to contact us is visiting our website. There you can find an explanation of the adoption process/ fees /requirements and you can follow a link to fill an adoption application. Thanks!  Www.RociosRescues.org
Thanks for wanting to make a rescue dog a part of your family!!

animal.description:
Meet Beau
This handsome boy needs you! Sweet, handsome, loyal Beau has been done wrong. Beau was originally surrendered after his owner’s house burned down three years ago. Beau and his dad were living in a car. Knowing there was more for Beau in life, Beau was surrendered to us in the hopes of finding a loving home. For months Beau was despondent. 
Then after more than a year, an older couple came for Beau. Before they adopted, we said Beau’s only issue is that he doesn’t like other dogs. He’s happy to just go out in the backyard and be with his people. We told them OVER AND OVER again and received assurance it wouldn’t be an issue. They had a big back yard, which Beau LOVED. He was happy… until his owners tried to mingle him with other dogs and walk him through the neighborhood where dogs roamed off leash. Unfortunately, for Beau he was considered too hard to handle when aggressively approached by an unleashed dog, not once, but twice.  Beau gave his whole heart to his new family just to be brought back to the shelter for defending himself.  They didn’t protect him and they didn’t love him enough to keep him safe at home. So now this handsome and near perfect dog is back at the shelter, confused and sad all over again. 
Beau is a 5.7 year old retriever/hound mix. Since being back he’s been incredibly sweet. He LOVES people, of all ages. He loves it when you sit in the yard with him. He loves sitting in the sun. Beau is house-trained and has wonderful house manners. He loves riding in a car and travels well. Beau is calm, sweet and affectionate. He’s absolutely the best companion anyone could ask for. All Beau wants is to be with his people. He doesn’t want dogs or cats, he doesn’t ask for a lot. He truly just wants to belong to people who love him.
If you are looking for an incredible companion to welcome to your heart and home, Beau is ready. He’s a love and he’s just about perfect. He will make your every day that much better. 
Call 706-865-4135 for information on additional health services provided as part of the adoption fee.  If interested in one of our puppies or dogs, please submit an application online or at the shelter. Applications can be submitted online at: https://www.charlessmithgallhumanesociety.org/page/dog-adoption-application 
Once an application is submitted online, you will receive an email saying your application has been successfully submitted.  If you don’t receive this email within 24 hours, please check to make sure all application fields were completed or please call our shelter at 706-865-4135. All adopters must complete an approval process which involves a reference check with current/recent vet and a brief home visit if located in the immediate area. We do permit out of state adoptions. Adopters MUST come to the shelter to transport their new family member home. We do not ship nor do we transport them to their new homes. Adoption policies and application procedures are detailed at the shelter website: http://smithgallhumanesociety.org/ under tab All Adoptable Animals.
Charles Smithgall Humane Society (CSHS) is a No kill shelter. Animals in our care remain safe with us until adopted. Resident animals are primarily owner relinquished and also accepted from local Animal Control. The facility usually is operating at capacity with a list of animals waiting for space to open.
Adoptions and meet and greets are being scheduled by appointment only. Please call our office, email us or complete an application and someone will be in touch just as soon as they can. 
Location: 4823 Helen Hwy., Sautee, GA 30571, Phone: 706-865-4135
Email: smithgallhumanesociety@windstream.net
Our shelter in Sautee GA is located about 3 miles south of the alpine town of Helen in northeast GA.

animal.description:
Meet Princess George, one of the three Cane Corso dogs abandoned in the depths of the Angeles National Forest. She was rescued in April and up until now she has been in a rehabilitation training to become a dog she was meant to be. 

Within weeks, this beautiful girl named Princess George, went from being frozen and pancaked from fear, to going on leashed walks with the pack and opting to join the others inside the house, thanks to her newly found appreciation of having a roof over her head. She is still so timid, scares easily and will continue to need so much supportive care and patience. But, we do feel at this time we can begin the search for her Forever home. A few mandatory essentials for our applicants include:
* prior large breed / Cane Corso experience.
* another dog in the home who is well balanced with medium and respectful energy.
* no children under the age of fifteen
* a calm household.
* a backyard that has fences and gates at least 6’ high.
* someone who is committed to ongoing training for an unforeseen amount of time. Our trainer will continue to be available as a resource.
And last but certainly not least:
* a kind, compassionate, intuitive heart who will have this girl’s back and will promise to love and protect her every day for the rest of her days.

Princess George is a pure, gentle creature who loves other dogs as well as her crate. She will lean her whole body against your leg and make you feel like you are the luckiest human alive. She’s around one-year-old and eighty pounds. She is a work in progress as are we all. Fully committed humans please apply.

Please submit adoption application through our website www.istandwithmypack.org/adopt

animal.description: Wisconsin is a total sweetheart! Just a young girl herself at around 1 year old, she came to Labs and More with 10 puppies. She's now ready to get back to the business of being a young dog and is looking for a forever family to call her own. We think Wisconsin is a mix of Shepherd and a sight hound like Pharaoh Hound- just look at those big beautiful ears! True to her Hound breed, her hearing, sight and smell are all on point. Wisconsin is housetrained and crate trained in her current foster home. She gets along with other dogs and adores her people. She can be wary of new people and dogs but once she has a moment to warm up, she lets her guard down and her curious, affectionate, silly personality comes out. She will bark at strangers and alert you when someone unknown comes up to the house. She loves to play with toys and lounge on the couch at night with you and watch TV. Wisconsin is wonderful on leash, letting you set the pace, and is very smart and treat motivated. If you are already approved with a coach or have adopted from us before, please reach out to your coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported, solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description: Graceland is the sweetest smartest gray lady youll ever meet! After having 9 pups, shes enjoying being the center of attention for once. She loves to play fetch, and soft, squeaky toys are her favorite. She LOVES to be cozy and comfy and is a great snuggler. However, shes not a fan of being left alone. Who is?! Even though shes fostering as an only child, she seems to tolerate cats and some other dogs. Shes great on a leash, and like a true Southern belle hates the cold and the rain. Always polite, she puts her paw on you to get your attention sometimes. She is a true gem.

PLEASE READ BIO BEFORE APPLYING

Brooklyn was rescued from a shelter in San Bernardino. 

Brooklyn (Brookie) is approximately 4 years old and weighs about 35 lbs. Brookie is a semi feral dog. We have had her a while and never posted her because she is amazing with other dogs and she is who we use to temp test dogs and we have just let her be. We have worked with her off and on but just recently we started working with her more because we have had the time to focus on her and she is making great progress. We can corner her in an area and can leash her. She is doing great on the leash. We can get her on the couch with a leash and she will relax and we can pet her. She takes treats from our hand and follows us around. She will jump up on the back of our legs for attention. She is not a barker. She wants the attention and love so bad but doesnt know how to receive it. She jumps up on the bed and she will nudge my hand and roll over for me to pet her belly. We are looking for an adopter for her that will take the time to work with her. Brooklyn is a very special girl to us. She would do best in a home with at least one other dog and a yard. He best furfriend is Molly who is also available for adoption. 

Brooklyn is ready to make some family very happy. She is available for adoption now so if you would like to be making memories with Brookie, complete an application: http://petstablished.com/adoption_form/4362/generic

animal.description:
Please read the dog's entire bio before you apply.  Sadly, we are no longer able to respond to every application, but will contact the one that is a good match within 3 days.
Kokonut is a female chilhuahua mix, 7-8 yrs old and 7-8 lbs.  She is very sweet, low key and so precious.    She comes up to strangers alwauys wagging her tail. Kokonut appears to be housetrained and does well with submissive dogs.  She did have a dental cleaning with some extractions and a mass removal and is doing amazingly well recovering and getting ready for her forever home.    She also has an eye condition (luxated lens) so she is on eye meds, at this point it is too soon to say if she will need surgery in the future, but for now her eye is stable.   She also has a MPL (loose knee) but that does not bother her at all.
Most of our dogs are not available to an out of the area adoption because of difficulty to follow up.  If you do not live within a 2 hr drive of Orange County, please email us before applying to see if the dog you are interested is may be a candidate for long distance adoption.    We only make consider long distance adoptions for dogs who have been in our rescue for 6 plus months with no local candidates.
If you are interested in adopting one of our rescues, please visit our main website for adoption procedures at www.pupsandpals.net and then fill out our application.  Please note that we are all volunteers so it may take up to 3 days to process your application, but you will hear back from us if your application is a good match for the pet. 
We do not have a shelter so individual appointments must be made to meet the pet you are interested in.  Our pets are fostered/boarded all over LA and Orange County.  
This pet is altered, vaccinated, microchipped, and has had a brief temperament evaluation to help us determine what type of  a home he/she would thrive in.  Please note that we put lots of time and effort to make sure our pets are ready to be someone's perfect pet before they go home.... and to make sure that we will have the best possible match for this pet we do require an : application, interview, adoption fee and in some case a home check.  
Listed for adoption: 11/20/2020
Adoption fee: $250
PLEASE DO NOT call or email to see if a pet is available.  We update our pages daily so if he/she is pictured here in the available dogs section, we are accepting applications at this time.

animal.description:
Meet Zayla and Tuxedo in Taos, New Mexico. They could be transported to Colorado for the right home!!!

Zayla and Tuxedo were found on a property where they were fending for themselves due to an unfortunate situation that had been going on for quite a while. A wonderful group of people made it their mission to save these 2 senior dogs along with several other animals that were left on the property, and they are now at a shelter waiting for a new home and family and happier days. 

Tuxedo is the handsome 11 year old Chow-Shepherd mix with a wonderful personality. He is starving for attention and love, and will nudge at you to keep petting him if you stop. He will even try to get all of his 60 pounds up into your lap if you let him. He has some arthritis and could stand to lose a few pounds, but he couldn’t be any sweeter!

Zayla is 14 years old and we think she is a Lab-Shepherd mix. She is the shyer of the 2, and looks to Tuxedo for reassurance and comfort. Zayla will warmup to people given time, patience and a gentle touch. If you crouch down and talk to her, her little tail will start going and you’ll know you are winning her over. Her arthritis is pretty advanced so we are looking for a home where she doesn’t have to navigate too many stairs. 

This sweet old pair has been through thick and thin together, so we are trying to find them a loving home together where they can be spoiled and live out their retirement as cherished furry family members. We think they would do fine with other respectful dogs. We are partnering with Stray Hearts Animal Shelter - Taos, NM to find Zayla and Tuxedo the retirement home of their dreams. Finding a home for a senior bonded pair can be hard, so please help us spread the word so that we can help make it happen. And if you are interested potentially adopting this amazing duo please fill out our online adoption survey: https://www.olddogsnewdigs.com/adoption-survey/
Thanks!!!

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior pets have a history of being kept up to date on vaccines, annual exams and recommended bloodwork. We also do home checks to make sure that your home environment meets the needs of the particular dog you are interested in.

If you’re interested in adoption, please fill out our online adoption survey at https://www.olddogsnewdigs.com/adoption-survey/

Caprese
Such a beautiful name for a beautiful girl.  We are guessing Caprese is 5 years old. She is a stunning gray brindled catahoula mix.  Her coat is so unique.   She and her brother Gravy were found on a busy highway laying beside their friend who had been hit by a car.  The lady that found them was sweet but a dog hoarder of sorts.  Her daughter finally got her to release them to rescue.  Gravy is living his dream life in New England.  Caprese stayed behind to be treated for a light case of heart worms but is now clear and in foster care in Bristol, RI.  She loves to walk and sniff and enjoy life.  She rides beautifully in a car.  She will need basic potty training but should catch on quickly.  Her brother was extremely shy and he is doing great with potty training.  I stay in contact with his sweet mom. She is an amazing girl and we are looking for an amazing family who realizes what a prize she is.  If you would like more info about Caprese please reach out.  Nobody gives better butterfly kisses than she does. However, she would need to be the only dog in the home.  She is fine with cats but if other dogs come at her quickly she will bare her teeth and growl as a defense.  She lived in my house beautifully with my 3 dogs and my kitten. She just is not the type of dog for a play date or a dog that rushes up to her and is all in her face.  She did well with children but think she would be better in a less active household without kids.  A calm household would be great for her.  I think this is due to the hard life she led before we rescued her.  She lived with many dogs in my barnyard kennels in free life style.  There was never an issue but she was the boss.  Don't let this dissuade you from asking about her.  She is amazing and deserves that forever home.  She would do best in a fenced yard for her potty training.  Before she left for Rhode Island, she moved inside with her Louisiana foster mom for almost 3 weeks before she left for New England and came to work with me for 7 days.  She met many customers and loved them all.  She is a beautiful girl with a stunning unique coat (almost Tiger like) that will make a great loving pet for that special home.

Adoption fees details: 
Puppies - Adults $ 550, Seniors $375. These adoption rates include transport from Alexandria, Louisiana to designated New England adopter pick up locations and NE foster homes using either Rescue Road Trips, Pets LLC or CAFA Transport. If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. Adoption fee breakdown:Adoption Fee:   $  365.00Transportation Fee:  $ 185.00MA and NH only--Quarantine fee if applicable:  $125.00

Medical details:
All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Bordetella, Heartworm tested with negative test results, microchipped, treated for parasites and on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention. A health certificate is issued by a licensed Louisiana veterinarian.

Adoption details:  
In some instances, a meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home in New England available. Available for a Meeting confirms the dog is in a NE Foster home and available for a meeting in the city state provided.  Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so, they go straight to adopters home. Foster parents talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters to let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we will ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged. 
Transport details:Rescue Road Trips (rescueroadtrips.com), Pets LLC (petsllc.net) or CAFA Transport will deliver our precious pups on commercial rescue animal transport to designated locations.  The fee is 185.00 which IS INCLUDED in your adoption fee already.**Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

MA and NH RESIDENTS:
If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence, an additional fee of $125.00 will apply due to State quarantine fee requirements. If the dog is in a foster home in MA or NH, this fee will be added in the adoption fee regardless of where the adopters home is located making the total adoption fee $675.00 for puppies and adults $495.00 for Seniors, otherwise the full adoption fee for all other states is $550.00 for puppies and adults and $375.00 for seniors. This includes a 48 quarantine, recheck by a MA licensed veterinarian, and issued a MA health certificate.

Visit all our available dogs at www.cenlaallianceforanimals.comWe update and add dogs frequently.

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.
