animal.description: Hi! My name is Ruby Blue (to highlight my beautiful coat and eye color,respectively).  I am a 2 yr old mini Aussie looking for my furever family. I was surrendered to the shelter by my former family because I was unable to keep food down and was losing a lot of weight. Luckily, I was rescued by Herding Haven and was given the medical care I needed.  It turns out that I have a rare neuro-muscular disease called Myasthenia Gravis.  It causes a complication called Megaesophagus which makes it hard for me to keep food down.  Fortunately, there is a medication that can treat this disease and since I have been on it I am doing so much better!  I still have to eat my meals (3 x day) in a special chair called a Bailey Chair (see picture).  But enough of the medical stuff.  Let me tell you about ME!  I am small in stature but big in personality.  I love car-rides, snuggle time walks and hikes.  I am never far-from your side (and would prefer that you are not far from mine!).  I crate-trained and will even sleep in the crate at night (although I would much rather share your pillow!). I enjoy playing with other dogs but would rather have my person all to myself in my new home.  I am spayed and up-to-date on my vaccinations.  If you would like to meet me (and why wouldn't you?), please contact kathie@herdinghaven.org

PLEASE COMPLETE OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AT WWW.LOVEBUGSRESCUE.ORG IF YOU'D LIKE TO MEET CARLO:

This handsome boy was surrendered by his former owner after he tied him up outside to avoid taking him to the shelter. Carlo is a 2 year old German Shepherd who weighs 80 lbs. This fun packed pooch doesn't have a care in the world and gallops along making new friends along the way. Carlo is great with other dogs and new people he meets. He came to us with no training under his belt, so he has a lot to learn. But the good news is, he's very food motivated and catches on very quickly! Carlo will do best in a home experienced with large breed dogs and someone who would like to take him through obedience training so he can get a few more skills under his belt. Carlo would love to go on daily outings such as long walks or hikes. He's truly magnificent with his long thick black tail and lanky build. No small kids due to his size and a home with some space and a yard would be ideal.

Carlo's adoption fee is $350 and that includes his neuter, registered microchip, vaccines current, deworming and flea treatment. Apply to meet him at www.lovebugsrescue.org

animal.description:
The infomation here is not a listing for a specific LPMR dog.   Instead it outlines the easiest way to adopt from LPMR at this time.  Please read before emailing with questions.
Due to the health risks with Covid 19, we are unable to hold our monthly meet and greet group gatherings. 

To continue to place our rescue pups with Families in the immediate Austin area we are asking interested adapters to fill out our online application. We have dogs coming in and being adopted on a regular basis. 

Filling out our application in advance allows us to have your application approved
And ready to go when a dog comes in that meets the applicants requirements. Then we are able to provide the adopter with all the information we have and immediately set up an individual meeting.  If that meeting goes well and everyone is in agreement we start our normal one week trial adoption. 

Adoption applications should be filled out to expedite the process:
http://www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org/joomla/adoption/adoption-application.html

Adoption fee $450
** The Texas Comptroller now requires sales tax on adoption fees.

*** Suspended due to COVID ***
Monthly Meet & Greets  (12:00 - 2:00)
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month


** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.
